{"term":"1960","caseName":"Lathrop v. Donohue","caseLink":"https://www.oyez.org/cases/1960/200","caseTranscripts":[{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - January 18, 1961 (Part 1)","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren7/oral_argument_audio/14277","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Number 200, Trayton L. Lathrop, Appellant, versus Josephine D. Donohue.","start":0,"stop":9.388,"duration":9.39},{"text":"Mr. Lathrop.","start":9.388,"stop":10.968,"duration":1.58}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the Court.","start":10.968,"stop":14.342,"duration":3.37},{"text":"This is an appeal from the judgment of the Supreme Court of the State of Wisconsin which was entered on April 5, 1960.","start":14.342,"stop":23.401,"duration":9.06},{"text":"This action involves the validity of rules of the Supreme Court of Wisconsin which requires that persons, who practice law in the State of Wisconsin, join, belong to and support an association of attorneys known as the State Bar of Wisconsin.","start":23.401,"stop":42.241,"duration":18.84},{"text":"Rules were adopted in the latter part of 1956 for a temporary period of two years.","start":42.241,"stop":48.658,"duration":6.42},{"text":"At the end of 1958, they were continued in effect, indefinitely.","start":48.658,"stop":53.441,"duration":4.78},{"text":"This action was commenced in June of 1959 to recover from the treasurer of the association, dues which were paid to him under protest.","start":53.441,"stop":63.828,"duration":10.39},{"text":"It’s contended that the rules violate the Fourteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution.","start":63.828,"stop":69.762,"duration":5.93},{"text":"There was a demurrer to the complaint.","start":69.762,"stop":71.627,"duration":1.86},{"text":"The Circuit Court sustained the demurrer and dismissed the action without leave to plead over.","start":71.627,"stop":78.98,"duration":7.35},{"text":"The -- upon appeal to the Supreme Court, that Court held that the rules do not violate the Fourteenth Amendment and affirmed the judgment of the Circuit Court.","start":78.98,"stop":89.175,"duration":10.19},{"text":"The jurisdiction of this Court is invoked under Section 1257 (2) of title 28 of the United States Code.","start":89.175,"stop":97.347,"duration":8.17},{"text":"The appellee asserts that there is no jurisdiction under said section on the ground that the rules of the Wisconsin Supreme Court do not constitute a statute under that section.","start":97.347,"stop":108.564,"duration":11.22},{"text":"This Court has repeatedly held over a period of more than 75 years that the word statute, as it's used, touched in the appellate jurisdiction of this -- this Court, covers all acts of a legislature -- legislative nature to which the -- the Court -- which the State gives its sanction and enforces.","start":108.564,"stop":127.521,"duration":18.96},{"text":"For example, it is stated that a city ordinance constitutes a statute, that a rule of Board of Regents of the University governing the conduct of students constitutes a statute, that a constitutional provision constitutes a statute.","start":127.521,"stop":144.954,"duration":17.43},{"text":"The -- the appellee asserts however that we have only a judicial act here.","start":144.954,"stop":151.889,"duration":6.94},{"text":"It is submitted what the appellee is -- is saying that is because of the nature of the body which creates the act that it is judicial rather than the nature of the act itself.","start":151.889,"stop":162.624,"duration":10.73},{"text":"We submit that it is the nature of the act which controls legislative powers defined as the power to make laws and laws defined as the aggregate of those rules and principles of conduct which the governing body recognizes as those which are enforcing sanctions.","start":162.624,"stop":178.53,"duration":15.91},{"text":"So it is respectfully submitted that the rules of the Supreme Court of the State of Wisconsin do constitute a statute.","start":178.53,"stop":187.612,"duration":9.08},{"text":"We further state that Wisconsin Supreme Court itself, states that they are part of the police power, is exercised pursuant to the police power and they're exercised pursuant to the policy making functions of the Court, and not pursuant to a -- an adjudicatory function of the Court.","start":187.612,"stop":205.566,"duration":17.95},{"text":"He was attended by the -- I should say that the argument is going to be divided between Mr. Isaksen and myself.","start":205.566,"stop":214.698,"duration":9.13},{"text":"Mr. Isaksen, will address himself to the free speech question and I will address myself to the question of freedom of association.","start":214.698,"stop":221.505,"duration":6.81}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I didn’t understand the divisions.","start":221.505,"stop":223.297,"duration":1.79}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Isaksen will address himself to the free -- free speech question and I will cover the question of freedom of association, Your Honor.","start":223.297,"stop":233.036,"duration":9.74},{"text":"It was intended by the Wisconsin Supreme Court that the Integrated Bar Association be a continuation of the previously existing voluntary Wisconsin Bar Association.","start":233.036,"stop":245.035,"duration":12},{"text":"That attention has been accomplished.","start":245.035,"stop":247.634,"duration":2.6},{"text":"The Integrated Bar started out with the same general officers, the same executive director, the same property, the same files, the same magazine.","start":247.634,"stop":256.813,"duration":9.18},{"text":"The Court rules provided that the integrated association shall elect their delegates to the American Bar Association previously elected by the voluntary association.","start":256.813,"stop":264.858,"duration":8.05},{"text":"Court rules provided that the integrated association shall elect the members of the state judicial council which were previously elected by the voluntary association.","start":264.858,"stop":275.976,"duration":11.12},{"text":"The integrated -- the rules and bylaws refer to the integrated association as an association over 60 times.","start":275.976,"stop":285.208,"duration":9.23},{"text":"The integrated association performs substantially the same functions and it's substantially the same manner as did the voluntary association and as does -- does the American Bar Association as it is alleged in the complaint.","start":285.208,"stop":297.645,"duration":12.44},{"text":"Complaint alleges that more than -- they're -- one of the main objects and purposes of the integrated association have been to promote law reform.","start":297.645,"stop":305.783,"duration":8.14},{"text":"Complaint alleges that the association makes and opposes proposals for changes in laws and constitutional provisions as the court systems, systems of selecting judges, text codes, corporate codes, property laws, criminal codes, laws among nations.","start":305.783,"stop":321.672,"duration":15.89},{"text":"And that the association has used its funds in opposition to the adoption of legislation favored by the plaintiff, contrary to the plaintiff's convictions and beliefs.","start":321.672,"stop":331.148,"duration":9.48},{"text":"The law reform activities of the association extend to the United States Congress.","start":331.148,"stop":334.807,"duration":3.66},{"text":"It had laws to the state legislature.","start":334.807,"stop":337.114,"duration":2.31},{"text":"A special subcommittee has been created for -- for federal legislation.","start":337.114,"stop":342.178,"duration":5.06},{"text":"The Wisconsin Supreme Court and in the opinion below, took judicial notice of the activities of the association in the legislative field and stated that in every instance, legislative measures advocated or opposed, have dealt with the administration of justice, court reform and legal practice.","start":342.178,"stop":359.908,"duration":17.73},{"text":"Since the court below took judicial notice and went beyond the complaint, this Court is entitled to take judicial notice of the same facts.","start":359.908,"stop":367.361,"duration":7.45},{"text":"A certified copy of the minutes of the Board of Governors and of the Executive Committee of the State Bar of Wisconsin, have been deposited with the clerk of this Court.","start":367.361,"stop":377.207,"duration":9.85}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"May I ask you, where is it, the quotation of the state rules that compel the lawyers to belong to the association? Where is that printed?","start":377.207,"stop":389.341,"duration":12.13}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"It's printed in the record, Your Honor, on -- Rule -- Rule 2, Section 2, provides that --","start":389.341,"stop":403.596,"duration":14.25}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Where is that?","start":403.596,"stop":404.041,"duration":0.44}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm sorry, I'm sorry.","start":404.041,"stop":404.863,"duration":0.82},{"text":"Well, look down at page 8 of the record.","start":404.863,"stop":409.036,"duration":4.17}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Of the jurisdictional statement?","start":409.036,"stop":410.848,"duration":1.81}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"No, on page 8 of the transcript of the record.","start":410.848,"stop":413.508,"duration":2.66}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, page 8?","start":413.508,"stop":414.533,"duration":1.03}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir and at the bottom of the page and there is one -- there is a section called enrollment, which requires that everyone enroll and it just --","start":414.533,"stop":429.469,"duration":14.94}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What is the penalty?","start":429.469,"stop":430.924,"duration":1.45}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"I beg you pardon?","start":430.924,"stop":431.787,"duration":0.86}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What is the penalty for failing to enroll?","start":431.787,"stop":433.967,"duration":2.18}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Alright, then on -- on page 9, in Section 4, states that no individual other than an enrolled active member of the State Bar shall practice law in the State or in anyway, any manner hold themselves out as authorized --","start":433.967,"stop":451.94,"duration":17.97}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What -- what is the law with reference to one who holds himself out or attempts to practice law --","start":451.94,"stop":458.285,"duration":6.35}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, I --","start":458.285,"stop":458.599,"duration":0.31}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- without permission.","start":458.599,"stop":460.405,"duration":1.81}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"He's subject to both the criminal penalty and I think he's also subject to being in contempt of court.","start":460.405,"stop":466.345,"duration":5.94}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Is a criminal statute included in your record?","start":466.345,"stop":469.197,"duration":2.85}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":469.197,"stop":470.527,"duration":1.33}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What is the penalty, do you know?","start":470.527,"stop":474.615,"duration":4.09}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I do not know.","start":474.615,"stop":477.718,"duration":3.1},{"text":"I'm sorry, but I do know that -- that I would be very effectively stopped from exercising my ability to practice law.","start":477.718,"stop":486.92,"duration":9.2}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What --","start":486.92,"stop":487.851,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Can you cite us to that before the argument is over?","start":487.851,"stop":491.298,"duration":3.45}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":491.298,"stop":492.15,"duration":0.85}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, is -- is that -- what do you set forth in your complaint as the -- as the greed -- as the palm that comes to you that when -- I was about to say, you're happily here so you can best tell, what this means to a particular fellow who doesn't want to join and doesn't want to be integrated.","start":492.15,"stop":511.49,"duration":19.34}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Your Honor --","start":511.49,"stop":511.948,"duration":0.46}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What -- what have you set forth in your complaint will follow, if this judgment of the Wisconsin Supreme Court stands?","start":511.948,"stop":521.469,"duration":9.52}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, it's stated in the complaint that that I am required by the orders of the Supreme Court and the -- all -- all of the truth --","start":521.469,"stop":529.717,"duration":8.25}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Where is that which -- could you -- if you could --","start":529.717,"stop":532.043,"duration":2.33}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"All of the -- all of the --","start":532.043,"stop":532.349,"duration":0.31}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Could you just return to the exact -- to the record.","start":532.349,"stop":537.501,"duration":5.15}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"The entire -- the entire rules which we were –","start":537.501,"stop":539.178,"duration":1.68}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"No, no, not the rules, but what you said is the damage your complaint or hurt, the hindrance upon protected freedom if not proper the interest --","start":539.178,"stop":550.021,"duration":10.84}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor --","start":550.021,"stop":550.246,"duration":0.23}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Where is it set forth?","start":550.246,"stop":551.3,"duration":1.05}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Following the --","start":551.3,"stop":552.891,"duration":1.59}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Page what in the record?","start":552.891,"stop":554.162,"duration":1.27}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Following the Court, the -- the system of -- of pleading into the State of Wisconsin has set forth the ultimate facts in this complaint.","start":554.162,"stop":561.964,"duration":7.8},{"text":"I have set forth the fact that I've been admitted to -- to practice law and now I am required to join this -- this association.","start":561.964,"stop":571.8,"duration":9.84},{"text":"And --","start":571.8,"stop":572.091,"duration":0.29}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, what -- what if I read it, not actually read it, right now, why wouldn't I -- what is there in it that you state that makes a difference from an invitation to join a fraternity?","start":572.091,"stop":583.127,"duration":11.04}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"It is the compulsory feature of it, Your Honor.","start":583.127,"stop":586.352,"duration":3.23},{"text":"I am required to join in this --","start":586.352,"stop":587.685,"duration":1.33}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, required means that if you -- the question is that Justice Black has been pursuing with you, required means that if you don't do something, it makes a difference.","start":587.685,"stop":596.621,"duration":8.94}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct.","start":596.621,"stop":597.115,"duration":0.49}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, what difference does it make?","start":597.115,"stop":598.279,"duration":1.16}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"It makes the -- the difference makes that I will no longer be able to -- to pursue the only livelihood for which I have been engaged.","start":598.279,"stop":608.789,"duration":10.51}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You mean you -- it --","start":608.789,"stop":610.621,"duration":1.83}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"And that's alleged in the complaint.","start":610.621,"stop":611.661,"duration":1.04}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You mean you couldn't argue a case before the Supreme Court of Wisconsin?","start":611.661,"stop":614.951,"duration":3.29}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, except in my own behalf.","start":614.951,"stop":616.231,"duration":1.28}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Do I understand it?","start":616.231,"stop":618.758,"duration":2.53}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"That's --","start":618.758,"stop":619.384,"duration":0.63}]},{"speakerName":"John M. Harlan II","textObjs":[{"text":"And you couldn't practice law at all?","start":619.384,"stop":621.231,"duration":1.85}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct.","start":621.231,"stop":632.286,"duration":11.05},{"text":"The -- there are specific illustrations of the activities of the Wisconsin Bar Association and the State -- State Bar of Wisconsin integrated association, which appear in the minutes and among these are comprehension -- comprehensive revision of federal law relative to tax liens, family law bill which among other things, forbids those who were divorced and have children from remarrying without permission of a circuit judge and which makes it a felony for attorneys to start actions for breach of commerce, appropriation of funds to a legislative counsel, judicial salaries, constitutional changes permitting increase of judicial salaries during the term of office, a proposal to repeal integration of the Bar, a proposal reducing the time for buying mechanics liens, constitutional revision of the court system --","start":632.286,"stop":684.723,"duration":52.44}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What did you say that was required with reference to a proposal to repeal the integration laws?","start":684.723,"stop":691.402,"duration":6.68}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"There was a proposal in the -- in the -- in the Wisconsin legislature which was opposed by this -- by the integrated association.","start":691.402,"stop":700.96,"duration":9.56}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You're now giving a list of --","start":700.96,"stop":702.786,"duration":1.83}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"These are some of the --","start":702.786,"stop":702.964,"duration":0.18}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- proposals by the Bar to which --","start":702.964,"stop":704.974,"duration":2.01}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"But these are -- these are the proposals that the Bar have either supported or opposed.","start":704.974,"stop":710.011,"duration":5.04}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And they maybe things to which you may or in fact do with which you in fact -- with which -- with which you may or in fact do disagree, is that it?","start":710.011,"stop":719.232,"duration":9.22}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, Your Honor.","start":719.232,"stop":719.87,"duration":0.64},{"text":"I -- I would like point out this -- this statement, whether I disagree or not, I think is entirely irrelevant.","start":719.87,"stop":726.852,"duration":6.98},{"text":"I belong for example, to a church and I like the church, but the moment that I'm told that I belong to that, I have to belong to the church is when I don't want to get out of it because I don't think that the State has any business to tell me that I've got to belong to it or that the State has any business to tell me that I got to belong to an association and when the association accepts that kind of relief from the State then in and of itself, the association becomes something which I am not attracted to and that I don't want to have anything to do with it.","start":726.852,"stop":756.699,"duration":29.85}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What you're saying is or are you saying this, \"If you can't be coerced to express even your convictions.\"","start":756.699,"stop":763.075,"duration":6.38}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"I beg your pardon?","start":763.075,"stop":763.752,"duration":0.68}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You -- you cannot be coerced by state action --","start":763.752,"stop":767.758,"duration":4.01}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"That's --","start":767.758,"stop":767.927,"duration":0.17}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- that should be --","start":767.927,"stop":769.1,"duration":1.17}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"-- it's even the --","start":769.1,"stop":769.377,"duration":0.28}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- keen to express your conviction.","start":769.377,"stop":771.123,"duration":1.75}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, sir.","start":771.123,"stop":777.652,"duration":6.53},{"text":"Another -- and one other -- one other proposal that has concerned me, at the present time, the Bar of Governors has -- has under serious consideration, a proposal for the -- establishing the Missouri plan for selecting judges in the State of Wisconsin.","start":777.652,"stop":792.053,"duration":14.4},{"text":"These are illustrated -- proposals and they're not at -- at all inclusive.","start":792.053,"stop":798.949,"duration":6.9}]},{"speakerName":"John M. Harlan II","textObjs":[{"text":"When -- when did you first have the Integrated Bar?","start":798.949,"stop":802.88,"duration":3.93}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"The Integrated Bar in Wisconsin was established as of the 1st of January, 1957.","start":802.88,"stop":809.6,"duration":6.72}]},{"speakerName":"John M. Harlan II","textObjs":[{"text":"What is the oldest of the Integrated Bars?","start":809.6,"stop":813.161,"duration":3.56}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"North Dakota in 1921.","start":813.161,"stop":818.641,"duration":5.48},{"text":"The -- the integrated association uses its executive director as the lobbyist and he's registered as a lobbyist pursuant to Wisconsin statutes which require registration and reports for personal contacts that are made of Committee hearings.","start":818.641,"stop":835.588,"duration":16.95}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Where is that in the record? Is that -- all these things is stated in the record?","start":835.588,"stop":839.447,"duration":3.86}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"This -- this is -- this is -- the statement that I make here is referred to in the brief, Your Honor, but it -- it appears -- it's some of the matters that the Court of the Supreme Court of Wisconsin took judicial notice.","start":839.447,"stop":851.28,"duration":11.83},{"text":"It does not appear in the complaint but as I said before, when the court below took judicial notice.","start":851.28,"stop":856.78,"duration":5.5},{"text":"In all fairness to me, this Court should be able to do so too and I have cited authority to the effect that what this law in fact, below, is also law in fact, in this Court.","start":856.78,"stop":866.12,"duration":9.34}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"In all the -- that you are telling us, we can find either in the complaint, in the record or in the judicial find --","start":866.12,"stop":875.305,"duration":9.18}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":875.305,"stop":875.507,"duration":0.2}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- knowledge expressed by the Court.","start":875.507,"stop":877.859,"duration":2.35}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, except as to the -- what the Board of Governors are doing as to establishing the Missouri plan which appears only in the -- in the last minutes of the Board of Governors and that has been deposited with this Court.","start":877.859,"stop":889.729,"duration":11.87},{"text":"It doesn't appear in -- in either of the -- of the printed documents, but you do have it in the certified copy of the -- of the proceedings of the State Bar Association.","start":889.729,"stop":905.374,"duration":15.64},{"text":"Other activities of the association include the study in curricular -- study the -- of the teaching methods in curricular law schools, the promotion of programs for post-graduate education of lawyers, interpretation of proper practice of law to other professions and work on a minimum fee schedule.","start":905.374,"stop":924.861,"duration":19.49},{"text":"And the association also outlines procedures for furnishing legal aid to the Court, but this -- the association, however itself does very little work in legal aid.","start":924.861,"stop":934.88,"duration":10.02},{"text":"It does -- its -- its work is in the form of encouraging or insisting the -- the voluntary associations which do that work.","start":934.88,"stop":945.558,"duration":10.68},{"text":"In connection with the interpretation of the proper scope of the practice of law, the association enters into formal agreements with various other private associations.","start":945.558,"stop":958.784,"duration":13.23},{"text":"It has it -- they have grievance committees and these -- the grievance committees supplement the work and activities of the Wisconsin Board of Bar Commissioners, an agency created by the legislature and which had been existed for many years and it has -- it has saved that agency only about $400 a year.","start":958.784,"stop":978.579,"duration":19.79},{"text":"The association is engaged in a public relations program to advance the public acceptance of objects and purposes of the association.","start":978.579,"stop":986.763,"duration":8.18},{"text":"That is alleged in the complaint.","start":986.763,"stop":988.913,"duration":2.15},{"text":"However, it does not allege, but does appear form the minutes, that it hires a public relations consultant and that when it felt that publicity should be given to show the good work of the association in securing the voluntary surrender of licenses of attorneys, the Committee -- the public relations man was consulted in a meeting of the Executive Committee to determine how press releases should be handled.","start":988.913,"stop":1010.337,"duration":21.42}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Does the state contribute anything to the Bar Association funds?","start":1010.337,"stop":1013.743,"duration":3.41}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":1013.743,"stop":1014.706,"duration":0.96}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What are the dues?","start":1014.706,"stop":1015.985,"duration":1.28}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"$15 a year.","start":1015.985,"stop":1020.046,"duration":4.06}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What is the relation of the -- of your Supreme Court to the -- to the schemes of this Integrated Bar?","start":1020.046,"stop":1028.559,"duration":8.51}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"The Supreme Court is the creator of it or is the -- is the body that -- that caused it come into existence.","start":1028.559,"stop":1036.044,"duration":7.49}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And it -- do any reports of the doings of the association at the Bar, go to the Supreme Court or to anybody?","start":1036.044,"stop":1042.862,"duration":6.82}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I believe there is a report that goes to the Supreme Court at the end of each year.","start":1042.862,"stop":1049.751,"duration":6.89}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You haven't got those copies of that about, have you?","start":1049.751,"stop":1052.365,"duration":2.61}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"I have a -- I have a copy of the -- attached to the jurisdictional statement of the budget of the --","start":1052.365,"stop":1059.098,"duration":6.73}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"No, no.","start":1059.098,"stop":1059.316,"duration":0.22}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"-- of -- of the -- of the expenditures which were -- I believe were reported to the Supreme Court.","start":1059.316,"stop":1062.983,"duration":3.67},{"text":"It'll appear at the last page of the jurisdictional statement.","start":1062.983,"stop":1065.535,"duration":2.55}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But -- but you -- as I inferred that there's a separate document called an annual report by the officers of the Bar that go to the Supreme Court?","start":1065.535,"stop":1073.266,"duration":7.73}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"I do -- I -- I believe that's so but I -- I cannot say it.","start":1073.266,"stop":1076.816,"duration":3.55}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And what's the theory or the -- does the statute make this a requirement of the budgets that go to the Supreme Court?","start":1076.816,"stop":1083.249,"duration":6.43}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":1083.249,"stop":1084.159,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Is it just of --","start":1084.159,"stop":1085.16,"duration":1}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"It's a matter --","start":1085.16,"stop":1085.613,"duration":0.45}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- relation – tenure relation.","start":1085.613,"stop":1088.045,"duration":2.43}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"It's a matter of a -- of the association making that report and maybe that the rules require, but I -- I do not think that's so.","start":1088.045,"stop":1101.898,"duration":13.85},{"text":"Integration in Wisconsin is part of a national law reform movement.","start":1101.898,"stop":1107.732,"duration":5.83},{"text":"It has been fostered and guided by the American Judicature Society.","start":1107.732,"stop":1112.284,"duration":4.55},{"text":"This, we believe, clearly appears from the -- the amicus curiae brief filed by this society and I should like to read from pages 3 to 4, a paragraph on -- from their brief.","start":1112.284,"stop":1127.173,"duration":14.89}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Whose brief, American --","start":1127.173,"stop":1129.363,"duration":2.19}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"American -- American Judicature Society brief.","start":1129.363,"stop":1137.324,"duration":7.96},{"text":"Pages 3 to 4 states at the bottom of page 3, \"From the outset, it was a main line of policy that the society would work chiefly in and through the organized Bar for the achievement of specific judicial reform projects.","start":1137.324,"stop":1157.972,"duration":20.65},{"text":"This was for the sound and sensible reason that people everywhere tend to be suspicious of outsiders coming in and telling them what to do.","start":1157.972,"stop":1167.294,"duration":9.32},{"text":"The burden of lobbying and campaigning must always be carried on by local residents of the state or community\" and then skipping a sentence, \"This meant that the correction of the weakness and deficiencies of the Bar would necessarily be a prerequisite to any substantial accomplishment and judicial selection, court organization procedure or other reform areas.\"","start":1167.294,"stop":1189.636,"duration":22.34}]},{"speakerName":"John M. Harlan II","textObjs":[{"text":"Tell me as a matter of interest do you have voluntary Bar associations as well?","start":1189.636,"stop":1194.006,"duration":4.37}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"We have county Bar associations.","start":1194.006,"stop":1195.718,"duration":1.71}]},{"speakerName":"John M. Harlan II","textObjs":[{"text":"Do they take the position before the legislature?","start":1195.718,"stop":1198.52,"duration":2.8}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, they do.","start":1198.52,"stop":1199.347,"duration":0.83}]},{"speakerName":"John M. Harlan II","textObjs":[{"text":"Do they take the position contrary to that of integrate laws, state laws?","start":1199.347,"stop":1204.2,"duration":4.85}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1204.2,"stop":1204.888,"duration":0.69},{"text":"That is not in the record, Your Honor, and it may or may not be.","start":1204.888,"stop":1208.376,"duration":3.49},{"text":"I -- I couldn't say it.","start":1208.376,"stop":1209.145,"duration":0.77}]},{"speakerName":"John M. Harlan II","textObjs":[{"text":"This is just on general --","start":1209.145,"stop":1210.484,"duration":1.34}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1210.484,"stop":1214.541,"duration":4.06}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I would presume that being lawyers, they sometimes disagree?","start":1214.541,"stop":1218.952,"duration":4.41}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I can say this that there is an undertaking by this -- by the state association to get the -- the county associations to channel all of their proposals into the state association and they work from there, so as to present one -- one front.","start":1218.952,"stop":1232.556,"duration":13.6}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1232.556,"stop":1234.443,"duration":1.89}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"I beg your pardon?","start":1234.443,"stop":1236.153,"duration":1.71},{"text":"-- I'm not saying there's anything wrong with it except that I don't feel that I should be compelled to support it, that's -- that's the question.","start":1236.153,"stop":1242.695,"duration":6.54},{"text":"And some other things if they do -- do like, I do not agree with, but that's -- the main question is whether or not, a person should be compelled to support an association.","start":1242.695,"stop":1255.186,"duration":12.49},{"text":"In 1946, the Wisconsin court held that integration could not be established for the purpose of conducting propaganda in defense of a legal profession or maintaining a legislative agent.","start":1255.186,"stop":1266.801,"duration":11.62},{"text":"In 1958, the Court specifically overruled the 1946 opinion.","start":1266.801,"stop":1272.673,"duration":5.87},{"text":"And Wisconsin court in the opinion below adopted the view of the Florida court, that the public welfare will be promoted by securing and publicizing the composite judgment of attorneys on matters affecting the administration of justice in the practice of law.","start":1272.673,"stop":1288.038,"duration":15.37},{"text":"The -- Florida court had held that discipline is not the reason for creating the integrated Bar associations.","start":1288.038,"stop":1299.557,"duration":11.52},{"text":"It is submitted that the Integrated Bar Association in Wisconsin is a political party.","start":1299.557,"stop":1305.836,"duration":6.28},{"text":"A political party is an association of men who are desirous of carrying out a certain line of public policy, to have that policy enacted in the law.","start":1305.836,"stop":1317.053,"duration":11.22},{"text":"Many times, a political party accomplishes this end by advancing and supporting candidates, but the objects of the party can be obtained just as well by influencing those persons who are already in office.","start":1317.053,"stop":1339.359,"duration":22.31},{"text":"Also, the ends of the party can be achieved simply by creating a climate of public opinion in favor of the party's principles.","start":1339.359,"stop":1350.373,"duration":11.01},{"text":"This Court has held on many occasions that freedom of association is guaranteed by the First and Fourteenth Amendments.","start":1350.373,"stop":1357.831,"duration":7.46},{"text":"It has held that the right of freedom association is a right of freedom of movement.","start":1357.831,"stop":1365.017,"duration":7.19},{"text":"It has held that the State cannot select its lawyers in such a way as to impinge upon freedom of political expression or association.","start":1365.017,"stop":1374.557,"duration":9.54},{"text":"However, the court below refused to recognize that there is a freedom not to join an association.","start":1374.557,"stop":1380.463,"duration":5.91},{"text":"It said that it is merely cliche to say that the freedom to associate includes the freedom not to associate.","start":1380.463,"stop":1388.872,"duration":8.41},{"text":"We submit that there cannot be a right to join an association, unless there is a right not to join an association.","start":1388.872,"stop":1396.669,"duration":7.8},{"text":"Otherwise, we are translating our rights into requirements.","start":1396.669,"stop":1404.958,"duration":8.29},{"text":"The framers of the United Nations Declaration of Human Rights did not regard freedom not to associate as mere cliche.","start":1404.958,"stop":1413.095,"duration":8.14},{"text":"They specifically provided that no one may be compelled to belong to an association.","start":1413.095,"stop":1418.368,"duration":5.27},{"text":"This declaration which was made at the end of World War II is highly significant and should not be lightly disregarded.","start":1418.368,"stop":1426.209,"duration":7.84},{"text":"In Italy, for example, in order for a man to go into business or to engage in farming or obtain employment or engage in his profession, he was required to either pay dues to or belong to his own syndicate and the syndicates were both political and economic.","start":1426.209,"stop":1447.296,"duration":21.09},{"text":"This was the corporate statement.","start":1447.296,"stop":1449.871,"duration":2.58},{"text":"We submit that the history of our Constitution and of our country, shows that the freedom not to join an association is a basic liberty guaranteed by the due process clauses and as well as the First Amendment.","start":1449.871,"stop":1462.974,"duration":13.1},{"text":"Just before the American Declaration of Independence in 1776, a French liberal minister Turgut, prevailed upon Louis XVI to free the French from the compulsory Guild System.","start":1462.974,"stop":1474.431,"duration":11.46},{"text":"We believe that Madison had in mind, the European compulsory associations, when he wrote that a free government is not a just government for arbitrary restrictions, exemptions and monopolies denied to part of its citizens, the free use of their faculties of which violates the property that individuals have in their opinions or which invades the conscience of individuals.","start":1474.431,"stop":1497.901,"duration":23.47}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"May I ask you this question?","start":1497.901,"stop":1500.796,"duration":2.89},{"text":"Is it -- do you imply by your argument or do you make the argument because of the implications that it carries, it would carry, if this statute were found not to be unconstitutional regarding the coercive power of a state to make people join all sorts of organizations.","start":1500.796,"stop":1520.636,"duration":19.84},{"text":"Is that the fear the considers --","start":1520.636,"stop":1521.811,"duration":1.17}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, I do.","start":1521.811,"stop":1523.108,"duration":1.3}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And does that mean that you would think that if this Court sustained this statute that the Milwaukee legislature could pass a statute of every able-bodied man between 18 and 45 must join the (Inaudible) Milwaukee?","start":1523.108,"stop":1537.974,"duration":14.87}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I suspect, Your Honor that that's -- that's what we're going to be led to.","start":1537.974,"stop":1542.259,"duration":4.29},{"text":"It will be -- first will be the -- first, it will be the accountants' association and then it would be the -- the doctors and the dentists and then of the beekeepers and those to hold taxi cab licenses and all the way up and down the line.","start":1542.259,"stop":1558.411,"duration":16.15},{"text":"I think that's what we're -- what we're headed for.","start":1558.411,"stop":1560.977,"duration":2.57}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But if you take one step, you must take six others.","start":1560.977,"stop":1564.564,"duration":3.59},{"text":"And he's one other -- he's one other, is that right?","start":1564.564,"stop":1566.008,"duration":1.44}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1566.008,"stop":1566.852,"duration":0.84},{"text":"I -- I think when we've taken this step here, we've already done it.","start":1566.852,"stop":1569.532,"duration":2.68},{"text":"Now, for example, we already have an integrated dental association in Oklahoma.","start":1569.532,"stop":1576.163,"duration":6.63},{"text":"Not only that, but other states have used other types of coercion perhaps in to cause people to join associations instead of an outright statements you have to join, they give governmental powers to the association and the -- and that members of the profession who do not belong or do not want to belong are in fact coerced to belong for their own protection.","start":1576.163,"stop":1600.537,"duration":24.37},{"text":"In South Dakota, the State Nurses Examining Board is appointed from list of names submitted by the State -- by South Dakota State Nurses Association.","start":1600.537,"stop":1609.738,"duration":9.2},{"text":"Also in South Dakota, the Board of Funeral Directors is required to be selected from a list of candidates nominated by the Embalmers and Funeral Home Directors Association.","start":1609.738,"stop":1619.873,"duration":10.13},{"text":"The appointment of Board of Dental Examiners is from the North Carolina dental society.","start":1619.873,"stop":1629.068,"duration":9.19},{"text":"Also, in North Carolina, four of the nine members of the Board of Health are elected by the medical society.","start":1629.068,"stop":1635.929,"duration":6.86},{"text":"Also in Alabama, the medical association has constituted the State Board of Health.","start":1635.929,"stop":1642.263,"duration":6.33},{"text":"We're already a long way.","start":1642.263,"stop":1645.632,"duration":3.37}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Are those associations all compulsory associations?","start":1645.632,"stop":1649.184,"duration":3.55}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, I think that they were made compulsory by the mere fact that the -- that the governmental power is given to these associations, but those are on the outside in effect, have to come in for their own protection.","start":1649.184,"stop":1664.863,"duration":15.68}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't quite understand that.","start":1664.863,"stop":1666.446,"duration":1.58},{"text":"That's not this case, in any event?","start":1666.446,"stop":1667.809,"duration":1.36}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Alright.","start":1667.809,"stop":1668.287,"duration":0.48},{"text":"I understand -- I understand it isn't, but if you give -- if you give a -- a board, disciplinary powers and you say that that board is to be elected by an association, the natural result is that the -- the association has a tendency to -- to protect their own members, but those who are on the outside are not so likely to receive the protection.","start":1668.287,"stop":1695.693,"duration":27.41},{"text":"If with this -- let's basically refer to the --","start":1695.693,"stop":1698.028,"duration":2.34}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that's not -- that's not your case here, isn't it?","start":1698.028,"stop":1700.475,"duration":2.45}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that, but I -- we were talking about how this is leading to where we're -- where we're going.","start":1700.475,"stop":1704.575,"duration":4.1}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"We have many other integrated --","start":1704.575,"stop":1705.664,"duration":1.09}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1705.664,"stop":1706.157,"duration":0.49}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- things as I understand it, the hairdressers and -- and the beauticians --","start":1706.157,"stop":1710.601,"duration":4.44}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Your Honor.","start":1710.601,"stop":1711.243,"duration":0.64},{"text":"I don't believe --","start":1711.243,"stop":1711.778,"duration":0.54}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Farmers?","start":1711.778,"stop":1712.508,"duration":0.73}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":1712.508,"stop":1713.616,"duration":1.11}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"They're not anywhere?","start":1713.616,"stop":1714.725,"duration":1.11}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"They're not integrated, I'm --","start":1714.725,"stop":1715.894,"duration":1.17}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Is anywhere -- any State?","start":1715.894,"stop":1718.028,"duration":2.13}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I can't make that broad statement, Your Honor.","start":1718.028,"stop":1721.104,"duration":3.08}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I thought they were.","start":1721.104,"stop":1722.028,"duration":0.92}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"[Attempt to Laughter]","start":1722.028,"stop":1726.728,"duration":4.7}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think it affects your case.","start":1726.728,"stop":1728.166,"duration":1.44}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Alright.","start":1728.166,"stop":1729.895,"duration":1.73},{"text":"And again, emphasizing the -- the freedom of association which was existing in this country, refer again to Tocqueville and his work on observation of democracy in America.","start":1729.895,"stop":1747.163,"duration":17.27},{"text":"In the first part of the 19th Century, he stated that freedom of association is one of the most fundamental rights and that no legislature can attack it, but on impairing the foundations of society.","start":1747.163,"stop":1760.066,"duration":12.9},{"text":"And in America, he said that no one abjures the exercise of his reason and his free will.","start":1760.066,"stop":1765.775,"duration":5.71},{"text":"Now, in view of these things that I've just stated, I think that one can now wonder whether or not, that isn't what we're coming to.","start":1765.775,"stop":1774.642,"duration":8.87},{"text":"The -- the compulsory association idea has been referred to as a matter of -- of group self-government by the appellee.","start":1774.642,"stop":1784.088,"duration":9.45},{"text":"Perhaps, the word group could better be left out of it and as a matter -- I meant the word, itself, could be left out so it's just a matter of group government, because for example, in -- in Missouri, the group government ideas brought about a constitutional revision giving the Bar Association equal rights with the Governor in the appointment of judges.","start":1784.088,"stop":1806.122,"duration":22.03},{"text":"And it's also shown in the national scene where the American Bar Association is seeking to obtain as a matter of regular course of procedure that the executive refer all proposals for the appointment of judiciary to the American Bar Association.","start":1806.122,"stop":1823.191,"duration":17.07},{"text":"And in view of these precedents in the case of lawyers, I say it's a small wonder that the group self-government proposals and -- and enactments which were involved in the Schechter Poultry case and in the Carter Coal case were enacted.","start":1823.191,"stop":1842.247,"duration":19.06},{"text":"So -- so small wonder that we have the compulsory features that appear in the Railway Labor Act.","start":1842.247,"stop":1848.841,"duration":6.59},{"text":"And in the Carter case, the majority of the Court held without disagreement of the minority on this point with the -- also with the concurrence of Chief Justice Hughes that, \"To permit a group, to make rules according to their own views of expediency so as to bind or disagree minority, violates the guarantees of liberty of the Fifth Amendment.","start":1848.841,"stop":1868.839,"duration":20}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"This leads me to ask whether you could expand on the question I put to you earlier.","start":1868.839,"stop":1874.828,"duration":5.99},{"text":"What is the connection and what is more particularly the authority that the Supreme Court has over the doings of the Integrated Bar?","start":1874.828,"stop":1888.528,"duration":13.7}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"The Supreme Court of Wisconsin, when it decided to integrate the Bar, adopted a group of bylaws and rules and then it said in a later opinion that if you -- if the Bar Association stays within these rules and bylaws, you're -- you're free and independent, you can do what you want.","start":1888.528,"stop":1915.392,"duration":26.86},{"text":"Now, that's the connection.","start":1915.392,"stop":1916.294,"duration":0.9},{"text":"They created it.","start":1916.294,"stop":1917.516,"duration":1.22},{"text":"They said, \"You got to belong, but when you're within these rules, you're -- the -- the association is free and independent.\"","start":1917.516,"stop":1923.959,"duration":6.44}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"Could I ask you, your view was the establishment of the Integrated Bar in the rules under which it operates by your Supreme Court state action?","start":1923.959,"stop":1935.265,"duration":11.31}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":1935.265,"stop":1938.673,"duration":3.41}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"And promulgated under the Supreme Court's inherent power to regulate its officers?","start":1938.673,"stop":1945.493,"duration":6.82}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"It -- it stated that that was the way that it was -- it was promulgating that, that's correct, under its inherent power.","start":1945.493,"stop":1951.714,"duration":6.22}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, then, would the State of Wisconsin have a right to impose an annual license upon you as a member of its Bar for the privilege of practicing law in Wisconsin?","start":1951.714,"stop":1965.011,"duration":13.3}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":1965.011,"stop":1966.362,"duration":1.35}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"Is that different than what is done?","start":1966.362,"stop":1968.726,"duration":2.36}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":1968.726,"stop":1969.727,"duration":1}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"In what way?","start":1969.727,"stop":1971.06,"duration":1.33}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Because the annual license of the -- such as the medical of -- medical man's license is paid to the State Treasury and it is used to pay representatives of the whole people appointed by the governor or the legislature, whatever it is, to regulate the profession.","start":1971.06,"stop":1992.9,"duration":21.84},{"text":"In our case, the dues are -- are paid to an association which is -- has not appointed as so-called by the -- by the governor, but it's this -- the association itself that decides what laws it's going to propose to -- to -- or -- or oppose and it's the association itself that has the grievance committees and so on.","start":1992.9,"stop":2018.695,"duration":25.79},{"text":"This is -- in other words, the difference is, in the one case and I think this is a very vital difference, in the one case, you've got government by representatives of the people as a whole, in the other case, you've got group or class government.","start":2018.695,"stop":2035.788,"duration":17.09},{"text":"There's a very real distinction and the question is whether or not, we're going to have that kind of government in this country.","start":2035.788,"stop":2044.919,"duration":9.13}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"What uses but not that he gives them to dissolve the Integrated Bar and not to stop then from practicing that might be unlawful or (Inaudible), is that what it is?","start":2044.919,"stop":2057.434,"duration":12.52}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"My view is that the Integrated Bar under the First Amendment -- that the Bar Association under the First Amendment, should be able to -- to take any position it wants with respect to legislation or -- or candidates or whatever.","start":2057.434,"stop":2072.19,"duration":14.76},{"text":"The association under the First Amendment should be able to do any of those things.","start":2072.19,"stop":2075.35,"duration":3.16},{"text":"The Court should not be able to come in and tell it that it can't do any of those things.","start":2075.35,"stop":2079.498,"duration":4.15},{"text":"My view is however, from the other end, that the state or the Court cannot tell me to support the association.","start":2079.498,"stop":2088.217,"duration":8.72},{"text":"The association itself can do what it wants, but it cannot support -- cannot compel me to support the association.","start":2088.217,"stop":2094.967,"duration":6.75}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm going to tell I want you to read and then compel you to pay an annual license fee for the privilege of practicing?","start":2094.967,"stop":2103.561,"duration":8.59}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Not to the association, Your Honor and pay it to the State to be administered by the representatives of the whole people.","start":2103.561,"stop":2113.16,"duration":9.6},{"text":"I think that's a very vital distinction.","start":2113.16,"stop":2115.22,"duration":2.06}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"Under the State and they (Inaudible) and the same amount of money the legislature to the State (Inaudible)","start":2115.22,"stop":2125.392,"duration":10.17}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":2125.392,"stop":2126.236,"duration":0.84},{"text":"I do not believe it could.","start":2126.236,"stop":2127.865,"duration":1.63},{"text":"My time is about up, I want to comment on -- on the Hanson case before I leave that is relied on continuously throughout the brief of the -- of the appellee.","start":2127.865,"stop":2143.08,"duration":15.22},{"text":"One construction of the Hanson case maybe that the Court believed that freedom of association would be infringed in that case, when the Government coerces an individual to support an association, but that the Court was of the opinion that it was required to waive the government interest in keeping open the channels in the arteries of interstate commerce as against the individual interest of freedom.","start":2143.08,"stop":2174.478,"duration":31.4},{"text":"And that in that case, the Court struck the balance in favor of the governmental interest.","start":2174.478,"stop":2180.678,"duration":6.2},{"text":"If that is the case, the Hanson case cannot be a precedent in a different kind of case where we are weighing different interest as against different facts or cannot even be a precedent even under the same statute where you have -- weigh different facts.","start":2180.678,"stop":2201.581,"duration":20.9},{"text":"So we submit that the Hanson case cannot be considered as a precedent in this case.","start":2201.581,"stop":2209.365,"duration":7.78},{"text":"However, if the Court does deem the Hanson case to be a precedent, we submit that there was an error in that case, a very serious error in that the Court did not determine whether or not, the interest of the Government in keeping open the -- the arteries of commerce was so great and so compelling as to be what this Court has called the compelling subordinating interest which required the invasion of the right of freedom of association.","start":2209.365,"stop":2237.93,"duration":28.57}]},{"speakerName":"John M. Harlan II","textObjs":[{"text":"Who do you think will decide that?","start":2237.93,"stop":2239.503,"duration":1.57}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Your Honor, you may have decided it, but it -- it does not appear from the opinion and it's -- it's a matter of a state -- it appears that it was left largely up to Congress to make that determination as to -- as to how the interest should be weighed.","start":2239.503,"stop":2258.359,"duration":18.86},{"text":"The Court itself did not appear to do it.","start":2258.359,"stop":2260.582,"duration":2.22},{"text":"It says, \"Congress has so determined,\" and this is within the -- the function of Congress and the Court did not make the determination.","start":2260.582,"stop":2268.266,"duration":7.68}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, but here -- here, the State made this determination in matters that are concerned of the state.","start":2268.266,"stop":2276.17,"duration":7.9}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"You Honor, I think it is --","start":2276.17,"stop":2276.919,"duration":0.75}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Here, wherein -- wherein is the power of the state to make a determination accommodating conflicting interest as to state matters, any different from the power of Congress as to matters confined to its competent.","start":2276.919,"stop":2294.058,"duration":17.14}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"Well -- well, Your Honor, the -- the Wisconsin court was familiar with the decisions of this Court requiring that there'd be a determination of compelling interest.","start":2294.058,"stop":2302.729,"duration":8.67},{"text":"And the Wisconsin court did not make such a determination and I am -- I am lead to believe that the Wisconsin court did not feel that it could say that there was such a compelling interest on the part of the state which would require attorneys to belong to this association.","start":2302.729,"stop":2314.877,"duration":12.15}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And on what basis did it sustain this?","start":2314.877,"stop":2317.112,"duration":2.24}]},{"speakerName":"Trayton L. Lathrop","textObjs":[{"text":"It merely attempted to weigh it as it appears that it was done in the Hanson case, merely saying, \"Well, this is a -- this is a valid government interest and we're just going to -- to sustain it.\"","start":2317.112,"stop":2326.751,"duration":9.64},{"text":"It did not attempt to see whether there was such a compelling interest as this Court has required.","start":2326.751,"stop":2336.494,"duration":9.74}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Isaksen.","start":2336.494,"stop":2337.523,"duration":1.03}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice, may it please the Court.","start":2337.523,"stop":2342.286,"duration":4.76},{"text":"A compulsory bar was not justified in Wisconsin and it is not existing as a means of disciplining the members of the Bar or educating the members of the Bar.","start":2342.286,"stop":2354.601,"duration":12.32},{"text":"It was not justified by the Supreme Court and it's not existing for the purpose of protecting the public from any incapacity on the part of the members of the Bar or any fraud or any deception or anything of that kind.","start":2354.601,"stop":2369.422,"duration":14.82},{"text":"What the Supreme Court did say in regard for the justification for this compulsory bar was this, and I'm substantially quoting, \"The public welfare will be promoted by securing and publicizing the composite judgment of the members of the Bar on matters directly affecting the administration of justice in the practice of law.\"","start":2369.422,"stop":2394.612,"duration":25.19},{"text":"It said further, \"The general public and the legislature are entitled to know the opinions of the majority of the members of the Bar.\"","start":2394.612,"stop":2405.656,"duration":11.04},{"text":"It said, \"The Court has determined that the public interest, that it is in the public interest, to have public expression of the views of a majority of the members of the Bar on these subjects.\"","start":2405.656,"stop":2419.72,"duration":14.06},{"text":"And it concluded that, \"The compulsory bar could do this job much more effectively than could a voluntary bar.\"","start":2419.72,"stop":2429.237,"duration":9.52},{"text":"In other words, if the Court please, this compulsory bar is existing and justified for the express purpose by the Supreme Court which created it, of securing and publicizing the opinions of men on the number of the subjects that relate to the administration of justice or the practice of law or court reforms.","start":2429.237,"stop":2450.936,"duration":21.7}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Does it have any disciplinary powers at all --?","start":2450.936,"stop":2453.751,"duration":2.82}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"It does.","start":2453.751,"stop":2454.643,"duration":0.89}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"It does.","start":2454.643,"stop":2455.28,"duration":0.64}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"It does.","start":2455.28,"stop":2456.155,"duration":0.88},{"text":"Yes, but subject to the discipline of the Supreme Court.","start":2456.155,"stop":2458.199,"duration":2.04}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, but the Court merely said that wasn't the -- the burden of that?","start":2458.199,"stop":2462.902,"duration":4.7}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"Never mentioned it.","start":2462.902,"stop":2464.068,"duration":1.17},{"text":"These are the reasons for the -- justifying the compulsory feature -- compulsory bar.","start":2464.068,"stop":2469.652,"duration":5.58}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Has it anymore disciplinary power in the full meaning of that term than the voluntary bar association had in Wisconsin?","start":2469.652,"stop":2478.015,"duration":8.36},{"text":"In other words, if the mechanism by which matters are brought to the attention of what ultimately is the determination of the Supreme Court, isn't that right?","start":2478.015,"stop":2486.835,"duration":8.82}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"It was the same under the voluntary party, it had the same discipline --","start":2486.835,"stop":2489.261,"duration":2.43}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh -- go on.","start":2489.261,"stop":2490.167,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"-- under the voluntary party.","start":2490.167,"stop":2492.156,"duration":1.99},{"text":"Now, we submit, if the Court please, respectfully submit that our Supreme Court erred first in this respect, that it found that there was invasion in fact of First Amendment freedoms in this case.","start":2492.156,"stop":2505.849,"duration":13.69},{"text":"The Court said, \"He is as free as before to express his opinions on any subject in any manner he wishes.\"","start":2505.849,"stop":2516.039,"duration":10.19},{"text":"And when it came to the balancing of interest in that part of its opinion, it said, \"When we attempt to balance the competing interest, we find no interference with the right of freedom of speech.\"","start":2516.039,"stop":2528.528,"duration":12.49},{"text":"Now, in determining whether there is an -- an interference in fact in this case, we must remember that the justified purpose and function of this Bar is to make public expression of the views of the majority of the Bar to be voiced through its Board of Governors.","start":2528.528,"stop":2547.016,"duration":18.49},{"text":"Now, what is the effect, if the Court please, on a member of the Bar who wishes not to speak or to remain silent or not take a stand on a bill before the legislature relating to divorce or to retirement of judges?","start":2547.016,"stop":2562.248,"duration":15.23},{"text":"It's impossible for him not to take a stand.","start":2562.248,"stop":2565.876,"duration":3.63},{"text":"The Supreme Court recognized in its opinion, that part of the dues and I'm quoting, \"are used to advocated causes to which he is opposed.\"","start":2565.876,"stop":2575.399,"duration":9.52},{"text":"So the mere fact of compulsory membership, compulsory payment of dues, one has taken a stand whether he wishes to or not.","start":2575.399,"stop":2584.548,"duration":9.15},{"text":"True, he has a choice of remaining silent and not taking a stand by resigning from the practice of law.","start":2584.548,"stop":2592.575,"duration":8.03},{"text":"It was held in one of the Jehovah Witness cases that a tax or a license fee cannot be exacted for exercising a freedom that's guaranteed or freely given under the Constitution.","start":2592.575,"stop":2605.043,"duration":12.47},{"text":"Here, the price of remailing -- remaining silent -- remaining silence is far more than a mere license fee.","start":2605.043,"stop":2611.778,"duration":6.73}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"In what way is the -- the petitioner come in conflict with the Integrated Bar?","start":2611.778,"stop":2617.755,"duration":5.98}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"In what way has he come in conflict?","start":2617.755,"stop":2620.512,"duration":2.76},{"text":"No way except that he is --","start":2620.512,"stop":2621.603,"duration":1.09}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then we don't have a case of controversy here.","start":2621.603,"stop":2624.206,"duration":2.6}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"I beg your pardon?","start":2624.206,"stop":2624.953,"duration":0.75}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Then we don't have a case of controversy.","start":2624.953,"stop":2627.047,"duration":2.09}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"He is sued for his dues.","start":2627.047,"stop":2628.761,"duration":1.71},{"text":"He paid his dues under protest, protesting that on the very grounds we're setting forth.","start":2628.761,"stop":2634.108,"duration":5.35}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, but in what way has his -- you're talking about his ideology and the Bar's ideology, but you haven't shown so far unless I've missed something, what the conflict was.","start":2634.108,"stop":2646.481,"duration":12.37}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"You mean a particular issue?","start":2646.481,"stop":2648.056,"duration":1.57}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, is there any -- has there been any conflict or is this just a --","start":2648.056,"stop":2651.088,"duration":3.03}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"On any particular measure?","start":2651.088,"stop":2652.375,"duration":1.29}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"-- a made up case there --","start":2652.375,"stop":2653.527,"duration":1.15}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"No, no, it's not a made up case.","start":2653.527,"stop":2654.731,"duration":1.2},{"text":"It's -- it's a payment of dues under protest alleging that we have to take a stand --","start":2654.731,"stop":2660.045,"duration":5.31}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"I know but is he -- has -- has the Bar taken -- been taking a position on issues that he disagrees with?","start":2660.045,"stop":2665.708,"duration":5.66}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, yes.","start":2665.708,"stop":2666.33,"duration":0.62}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"What are those issues?","start":2666.33,"stop":2667.222,"duration":0.89},{"text":"They don't -- I don't find them.","start":2667.222,"stop":2668.614,"duration":1.39}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"There -- there -- there's a general allegation in the complaint that they have done so and that's all we have to allege under our pleadings and that's admitted under the demurrer that they have done so and the Supreme Court has said so, that part of the dues are used for that purpose.","start":2668.614,"stop":2682,"duration":13.39}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"But we don't know what those issues are.","start":2682,"stop":2683.241,"duration":1.24}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"No, no, that's correct.","start":2683.241,"stop":2686.111,"duration":2.87},{"text":"Now, so that in order for this man not to take --","start":2686.111,"stop":2689.528,"duration":3.42}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) state or if the Bar Association will ever represent whoever is the respondent, is it claimed that in fact, they did not express views?","start":2689.528,"stop":2698.835,"duration":9.31}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"No, I don't think it's claimed --","start":2698.835,"stop":2699.715,"duration":0.88}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Is it claimed that they did not express views in all sorts of subjects?","start":2699.715,"stop":2703.449,"duration":3.73}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"It's admitted that they took positions contrary to his and to which he objected, that's admitted in the case.","start":2703.449,"stop":2709.332,"duration":5.88}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"On -- on matters that come within the confines of -- of their functioning scope, is that it?","start":2709.332,"stop":2714.975,"duration":5.64}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct.","start":2714.975,"stop":2716.408,"duration":1.43}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And their functioning scope is just the kind of questions that the Chief Justice would earlier, salaries of justice that of judges at tenure, etcetera, etcetera?","start":2716.408,"stop":2725.321,"duration":8.91}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"Right, any number of questions that relate to the administration of justice.","start":2725.321,"stop":2729.946,"duration":4.63},{"text":"Now, so that a man does have a choice of remaining silent or not taking a stand by resigning from the profession, that's the only way he can refrain from taking a stand on legislation.","start":2729.946,"stop":2742.933,"duration":12.99},{"text":"The price is too high.","start":2742.933,"stop":2744.886,"duration":1.95},{"text":"It means his profession.","start":2744.886,"stop":2746.966,"duration":2.08},{"text":"And as a matter of fact, the overwhelming majority of the Bar cannot afford not to take a stand.","start":2746.966,"stop":2752.66,"duration":5.69},{"text":"So they have two other choices, one is to say nothing and as do violence to the conscience or to -- to speak out himself, in order to disassociate himself from the majority view.","start":2752.66,"stop":2766.26,"duration":13.6},{"text":"And in order to do that, he also has to speak in a louder voice so to speak, in order to offset the majority voice which has been amplified with the dues that he's had to pay to help amplify the majority voice.","start":2766.26,"stop":2779.912,"duration":13.65},{"text":"Now, what if the person who wishes to speak on a particular measure?","start":2779.912,"stop":2784.588,"duration":4.68},{"text":"His rights are impaired because his voice is still.","start":2784.588,"stop":2787.885,"duration":3.3},{"text":"It's stilled at least to the extent that his -- the effect of his voice is minimized by the amplification of the majority voice, but it's still by a much more subtle force, we submit.","start":2787.885,"stop":2801.121,"duration":13.24},{"text":"This is -- a compulsory bar was created by our highest court.","start":2801.121,"stop":2805.584,"duration":4.46},{"text":"It has supervision of this bar.","start":2805.584,"stop":2807.748,"duration":2.16},{"text":"It retains supervision of this compulsory bar.","start":2807.748,"stop":2810.882,"duration":3.13},{"text":"It has -- they say as regard with mission of lawyers in regard to the discipline of lawyers, we practice before that Supreme Court.","start":2810.882,"stop":2819.092,"duration":8.21},{"text":"Now, his Court has said that there shall be public expression of the views of the majority of the Bar through the Board of Governors.","start":2819.092,"stop":2829.582,"duration":10.49},{"text":"Inevitably, the view of the Board of Governors tends to become the official -- the official, the orthodox view.","start":2829.582,"stop":2838.289,"duration":8.71},{"text":"And inevitably, the tendency would be to avoid a view that is unorthodox that isn't in accordance with the official body that's created by the Supreme Court.","start":2838.289,"stop":2848.163,"duration":9.87},{"text":"If for no other reason, then that one would take the attitude where there's no use.","start":2848.163,"stop":2853.501,"duration":5.34},{"text":"Money, they've got all the money.","start":2853.501,"stop":2855.164,"duration":1.66},{"text":"They're doing the work on this particular view, my voice is minimized and there are other reasons why it would be discouraged.","start":2855.164,"stop":2863.104,"duration":7.94}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Does the State Bar conduct the examinations for lawyers?","start":2863.104,"stop":2867.689,"duration":4.59}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"The State Bar commissioners, state court of (Inaudible)","start":2867.689,"stop":2870.89,"duration":3.2}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, but are --","start":2870.89,"stop":2871.688,"duration":0.8}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"-- separate arguments.","start":2871.688,"stop":2872.359,"duration":0.67}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- are they a part of the -- of -- of this organization?","start":2872.359,"stop":2875.17,"duration":2.81}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"They are not.","start":2875.17,"stop":2875.884,"duration":0.71}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"They are not.","start":2875.884,"stop":2877.794,"duration":1.91}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"It seems that is this discouraging of exercising one's First Amendment freedom that is possibly the greatest evil.","start":2877.794,"stop":2886.913,"duration":9.12},{"text":"This Court has said many times and once through, Mr. Chief Justice Hughes in the DeJonge case, free discussing of ideas -- it is the free discussing of ideas that results in change by lawful means.","start":2886.913,"stop":2900.237,"duration":13.32},{"text":"And in the Watkins case, the Court said, \"The absence of the unorthodox voice would be symptom of grave illness in the society.\"","start":2900.237,"stop":2908.353,"duration":8.12},{"text":"This compulsory bar tends to stipple the unorthodox, the unpopular view.","start":2908.353,"stop":2913.72,"duration":5.37},{"text":"And the result of the stultifying conformity which in one opinion of this Court said could be more dangerous in the long run than a foreign agent.","start":2913.72,"stop":2921.518,"duration":7.8},{"text":"Now, it isn't only the voice of the one who wishes to speak or doesn't wish to speak that is still or impaired, but the public's rights are impaired.","start":2921.518,"stop":2931.259,"duration":9.74}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"May I ask you please, Mr. Isaksen?","start":2931.259,"stop":2933.739,"duration":2.48},{"text":"Is all action of the Board of Governors subject to approval by or rejection upon vote of the members on the floor at your annual meeting?","start":2933.739,"stop":2945.257,"duration":11.52}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"No, they -- no, they are representatives and they have their own powers.","start":2945.257,"stop":2949.366,"duration":4.11},{"text":"They're elected by the members.","start":2949.366,"stop":2951.733,"duration":2.37}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"In other words, the members have no voice to override the recommendations of the Board of Governors?","start":2951.733,"stop":2959.522,"duration":7.79}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"There's a referendum, my partner tells me that, it could by referendum.","start":2959.522,"stop":2962.906,"duration":3.38}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"Just like in Missouri Act, do you know?","start":2962.906,"stop":2966.655,"duration":3.75}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not familiar with that.","start":2966.655,"stop":2968.726,"duration":2.07}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Has he bounds all that within the bounds of the job speak out?","start":2968.726,"stop":2973.572,"duration":4.85}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"No --","start":2973.572,"stop":2974.166,"duration":0.59}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"One that speaks --","start":2974.166,"stop":2975.509,"duration":1.34}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"-- one may speak out and speak out on the meetings, certainly.","start":2975.509,"stop":2978.42,"duration":2.91}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible) suppose they can have their own --","start":2978.42,"stop":2980.983,"duration":2.56}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, certainly -- certainly.","start":2980.983,"stop":2982.711,"duration":1.73},{"text":"One may speak, Your Honor.","start":2982.711,"stop":2984.359,"duration":1.65},{"text":"Yes.","start":2984.359,"stop":2985.478,"duration":1.12}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, they could do that under (Inaudible) for these claimants?","start":2985.478,"stop":2988.73,"duration":3.25}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"That is right.","start":2988.73,"stop":2990.026,"duration":1.3},{"text":"They couldn't do with that.","start":2990.026,"stop":2991.909,"duration":1.88},{"text":"We also feel that the public is entitled to be free from this majority voice, this amplified voice bombarded on the public and I think that's the spirit of only mentioning in the Public Utilities case versus Pollak where they had the programs, I believe was on the transit system.","start":2991.909,"stop":3010.828,"duration":18.92},{"text":"Here, we have a situation if the Court please, where the Government, the judiciary, forces opinions, publicizes them with the expressed purpose of influencing legislation in the legislative branch of the Government.","start":3010.828,"stop":3025.922,"duration":15.09},{"text":"This Court has said time and again, it's not the function of Government to keep the citizen from falling into error.","start":3025.922,"stop":3032.049,"duration":6.13},{"text":"Authority here, it is said, is to be controlled by public opinion, not public opinion by authority.","start":3032.049,"stop":3038.914,"duration":6.87},{"text":"And in the Watkins case, the very purpose of the First Amendment is to foreclose public authority from assuring a guardianship of the public mind.","start":3038.914,"stop":3048.476,"duration":9.56},{"text":"So we feel that the public is entitled to be protected against this government authority getting opinions and securing and publicizing them.","start":3048.476,"stop":3057.769,"duration":9.29},{"text":"Now, we feel that the Wisconsin court also erred in another important aspect as a matter law, when it said that the public and the legislature are entitled to know the opinions of a majority of the members of a bar.","start":3057.769,"stop":3072.826,"duration":15.06},{"text":"Under the decisions as we see them, except under the most extraordinary circumstances and compelling circumstances for Government isn't least concerned with the opinions of man.","start":3072.826,"stop":3083.496,"duration":10.67},{"text":"This Court has quoted on more than one occasion the opinions of men are not the object of civil government.","start":3083.496,"stop":3089.611,"duration":6.11},{"text":"This has been stated many ways, what a man thinks is of no concern to Government.","start":3089.611,"stop":3094.082,"duration":4.47},{"text":"I think we must let his mind alone.","start":3094.082,"stop":3096.544,"duration":2.46},{"text":"Here, we have a vehicle created for the express purpose of obtaining and publicize private opinions.","start":3096.544,"stop":3104.447,"duration":7.9},{"text":"And as a condition precedent to practicing law, to earning a living, I have to agree to voice that opinion on matters of great public concern, before I even know the subject is or how it's going to affect me.","start":3104.447,"stop":3118.892,"duration":14.44},{"text":"It seems that it has some of the characteristics of the old (Inaudible).","start":3118.892,"stop":3123.415,"duration":4.52},{"text":"It reminds one of the remonstrances of Madison against taxing those who do not believe for the support of those who do believe.","start":3123.415,"stop":3131.781,"duration":8.37},{"text":"It seems to have some kinship with the licensing of the press, the same logic.","start":3131.781,"stop":3136.563,"duration":4.78},{"text":"This is a privilege.","start":3136.563,"stop":3137.782,"duration":1.22},{"text":"We'll do a better the job for the profession itself.","start":3137.782,"stop":3140.958,"duration":3.18},{"text":"We'll do a better job for the public and so on, the same -- the same logic.","start":3140.958,"stop":3146.406,"duration":5.45},{"text":"In the Konigsberg case, this Court said, that is the Bar case to California, admission to bar case, \"If the license for admission to the bar was refused unless he answered questions relating to his political philosophy, then we would be compelled to decide far-reaching and complex questions relating to freedom of speech.\"","start":3146.406,"stop":3168.392,"duration":21.99},{"text":"We think we've reached the question in this case.","start":3168.392,"stop":3175.228,"duration":6.84},{"text":"This is a different type of free speech case than usually comes before the Court, its forced affirmation as distinguished from merely a -- a suppression of expression.","start":3175.228,"stop":3187.849,"duration":12.62},{"text":"There are relatively few cases of this type.","start":3187.849,"stop":3190.995,"duration":3.15},{"text":"We have the flag salute case, where the Court said, it's a compulsion to state of belief.","start":3190.995,"stop":3196.255,"duration":5.26},{"text":"The Senate -- it requires affirmation of a state of mind.","start":3196.255,"stop":3208.84,"duration":12.59},{"text":"That was reversed.","start":3208.84,"stop":3201.872,"duration":-6.97},{"text":"We have the California tax exemption case, Speiser v. Randall.","start":3201.872,"stop":3206.87,"duration":5},{"text":"We have the Konigsberg case.","start":3206.87,"stop":3210.317,"duration":3.45},{"text":"We have similar cases such as the -- the Sweezy and the Rumely, where it wasn't a belief, but stating some facts, those were all reversed.","start":3210.317,"stop":3217.735,"duration":7.42}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"When -- when the union -- labor union case was under argument a little while ago, one of the lawyers for the protesting member, I think stated that -- conceded that use of the funds for purposes of collective bargaining was legitimate as the use of the funds for other purposes what -- whatever he called, political purposes in that complaint, they were objected to.","start":3217.735,"stop":3247.081,"duration":29.35},{"text":"Can you think in this case of any legitimate use of the Integrated Bar’s funds for any project?","start":3247.081,"stop":3256.909,"duration":9.83}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, we have no objection, nobody objects to paying a fee and certainly, this fee is reasonable and submitting to the discipline and paying for the discipline and the Court doing the usual things that it can with regard to the officers of the Court, but I can think of no case where we have to -- where we are forced to belong to an association.","start":3256.909,"stop":3282.172,"duration":25.26}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"-- well that -- that that's belonging.","start":3282.172,"stop":3283.623,"duration":1.45},{"text":"I'm not talking about that.","start":3283.623,"stop":3284.627,"duration":1},{"text":"I'm talking about your point of freedom of speech.","start":3284.627,"stop":3287.178,"duration":2.55}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":3287.178,"stop":3288.011,"duration":0.83},{"text":"Is there anything for which it could be used, the money could be used?","start":3288.011,"stop":3291.553,"duration":3.54},{"text":"Now if it's forced?","start":3291.553,"stop":3293.199,"duration":1.65},{"text":"Unless there is a countervailing public interest that would justify such a thing, but we don't have that and I'm coming to that in just a moment.","start":3293.199,"stop":3300.43,"duration":7.23}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, of course we don't know under this complaint what these -- what the controversies are between the Bar and --","start":3300.43,"stop":3305.581,"duration":5.15}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"We know what -- we know what the Court said in -- in --","start":3305.581,"stop":3308.068,"duration":2.49}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"We don't know, are they, for example, the -- whether Wisconsin should -- should adopt the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure?","start":3308.068,"stop":3318.948,"duration":10.88},{"text":"Whether Wisconsin should adopt the Federal Rules of Criminal Procedure?","start":3318.948,"stop":3323.843,"duration":4.89}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"The Court --","start":3323.843,"stop":3324.178,"duration":0.34}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Whether Wisconsin should adopt a public defender system?","start":3324.178,"stop":3328.186,"duration":4.01}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"The Court --","start":3328.186,"stop":3328.976,"duration":0.79}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Are those all illegitimate activities?","start":3328.976,"stop":3332.929,"duration":3.95}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"If it's a forced organization, yes.","start":3332.929,"stop":3336.193,"duration":3.26},{"text":"No one has -- can compel me to pay to support the view on any of those unless --","start":3336.193,"stop":3340.729,"duration":4.54}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"There -- there is no -- not in this case, there's no even small circle of --","start":3340.729,"stop":3344.635,"duration":3.91}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":3344.635,"stop":3344.871,"duration":0.24}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"-- activities that --","start":3344.871,"stop":3345.875,"duration":1}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"The only -- the only activity and it is the big activity and the Court says, it's the securing and publicizing of opinions to put them before the legislature and the public.","start":3345.875,"stop":3356.377,"duration":10.5},{"text":"That's --","start":3356.377,"stop":3356.962,"duration":0.59}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- in your state, does every lawyer agree that a public defender system is desirable?","start":3356.962,"stop":3361.434,"duration":4.47}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"That a public what?","start":3361.434,"stop":3362.329,"duration":0.89}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That the public defender system is the desirable way --","start":3362.329,"stop":3365.342,"duration":3.01}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't -- I wouldn't -- I wouldn't --","start":3365.342,"stop":3365.949,"duration":0.61}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- taking -- taking -- of remedying a real evil.","start":3365.949,"stop":3369.258,"duration":3.31},{"text":"Has every lawyer in Wisconsin agreed on that?","start":3369.258,"stop":3371.787,"duration":2.53}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"I would -- wouldn't suppose that they --","start":3371.787,"stop":3373.672,"duration":1.89}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I should think the great division of opinion on that subject -- might have penetrated even Wisconsin.","start":3373.672,"stop":3378.434,"duration":4.76}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":3378.434,"stop":3378.807,"duration":0.37}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"You probably couldn't get every lawyer in Wisconsin to agree on any subject.","start":3378.807,"stop":3382.735,"duration":3.93}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":3382.735,"stop":3384.383,"duration":1.65}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That's every lawyer.","start":3384.383,"stop":3385.822,"duration":1.44}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":3385.822,"stop":3386.911,"duration":1.09},{"text":"That's right.","start":3386.911,"stop":3388.862,"duration":1.95},{"text":"We have had the employment cases.","start":3388.862,"stop":3391.526,"duration":2.66},{"text":"The only cases that I know of were -- we've gone into -- the Court has sustained getting opinion and they're apparently on the basis that it has some relation to competency and so on.","start":3391.526,"stop":3403.525,"duration":12},{"text":"Now, what is the -- the compelling interest on the part of the State here to justify this invasion into private opinion, this publicizing and securing a private opinion?","start":3403.525,"stop":3415.2,"duration":11.67},{"text":"There isn't in this case, any claim of any public evil or any great public danger or of any -- anything of that kind.","start":3415.2,"stop":3422.229,"duration":7.03},{"text":"There's no interference here with the operation of the Government or the functions of the Government or anything of that kind.","start":3422.229,"stop":3428.433,"duration":6.2},{"text":"The only thing the Supreme Court says is, it's for the public good that we have these opinions of the lawyers and they be -- and -- and you pay and the Board of Governors voice those opinions.","start":3428.433,"stop":3440.764,"duration":12.33},{"text":"That's all we have.","start":3440.764,"stop":3441.11,"duration":0.35}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But you -- your argument suggests -- your argument suggests that some better reasons could be found for the conclusion of the Wisconsin Supreme Court than it gave, but if better reasons can be found and they must be attributed to that Court.","start":3441.11,"stop":3456.785,"duration":15.67}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think they can be attributed to the Court, but there's --","start":3456.785,"stop":3458.859,"duration":2.07}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then -- then you must say as I suggest that you do say, but if they spelled all these out, it still would've been a coercion that involved and in fact you may go right to be free from having a coerced opinion expressly.","start":3458.859,"stop":3474.333,"duration":15.47}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"I should say, Mr. Justice Frankfurter that they're possibly are situations where the invasions of ones opinion are just that.","start":3474.333,"stop":3480.728,"duration":6.39}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"No, I'm talking about this case.","start":3480.728,"stop":3482.101,"duration":1.37},{"text":"I'm talking about if an Integrated Bar can be justified by considerations that saved it -- that saved this scheme from unconstitutionality, that saves the -- the rule -- the ruling of your Supreme Court from unconstitutionality, then the mere fact that the Wisconsin Supreme Court has written as good as opinion as could be written, would be immaterial, wouldn't it?","start":3482.101,"stop":3506.929,"duration":24.83}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think so, because this is the --","start":3506.929,"stop":3508.761,"duration":1.83}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You mean to say, we're bound by the insight and the literary skill and the economy of time at the disposal of the state courts in deciding whether a statute is constitutional or not.","start":3508.761,"stop":3519.28,"duration":10.52}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"I have no --","start":3519.28,"stop":3520.096,"duration":0.82}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Because for anyone of those reasons, if they didn't write the opinion satisfactorily or some other member of that court thought as could've written a better opinion, it's concealed on -- under the anonymity of per curiam.","start":3520.096,"stop":3532.198,"duration":12.1}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"Your -- Your Honor, I don't think that the Court could do it under the -- this circumstance of this case because --","start":3532.198,"stop":3538.137,"duration":5.94}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, then that's all -- if you say that, then you say -- then there's no complaint about they didn't give this reason or that reason.","start":3538.137,"stop":3545.319,"duration":7.18},{"text":"Then your position is that no reasons could vindicate this.","start":3545.319,"stop":3548.639,"duration":3.32}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"I say that -- I say that the Court has decided what this organization is for.","start":3548.639,"stop":3553.845,"duration":5.21},{"text":"It created the organization.","start":3553.845,"stop":3555.224,"duration":1.38},{"text":"This is what is to do.","start":3555.224,"stop":3556.221,"duration":1},{"text":"We have to take the Court's word as to what it is and that's what it is and we say that is not a compelling reason, it's not a justifiable invasion.","start":3556.221,"stop":3564.858,"duration":8.64}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You can't read -- at least I can read the opinion as saying, \"Only this and nothing more.\"","start":3564.858,"stop":3572.572,"duration":7.71},{"text":"It gives -- it makes a long speech about the -- the help that expressions of opinion give also stating right along side of it, the complete freedom to the individual to have his say, doesn't it, this opinion?","start":3572.572,"stop":3586.973,"duration":14.4},{"text":"This opinion says, despite the mobilization of professional opinion through this mechanism --","start":3586.973,"stop":3595.183,"duration":8.21}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"Right.","start":3595.183,"stop":3595.409,"duration":0.23}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- any member and every member of the Bar can have his say.","start":3595.409,"stop":3598.442,"duration":3.03}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":3598.442,"stop":3599.126,"duration":0.68},{"text":"The Supreme Court says so and we say that that is error because it cannot be true because we have had to pay our funds which are used for the purpose of this organization, which is to get the opinions of the majority of the Bar.","start":3599.126,"stop":3611.013,"duration":11.89}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that's your -- that's your real issue in it, whether you can be compelled to pay money --","start":3611.013,"stop":3614.906,"duration":3.89}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"That is --","start":3614.906,"stop":3615.207,"duration":0.3}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- enter a fund which will be used in part, to propagate views that you're against, whether the State can compel you to pay the money for that purpose.","start":3615.207,"stop":3627.028,"duration":11.82}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"Or -- or to the law, both of them.","start":3627.028,"stop":3629.509,"duration":2.48}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you think that's (Inaudible) directly (Inaudible) this Bar --","start":3629.509,"stop":3634.556,"duration":5.05}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"Right.","start":3634.556,"stop":3634.818,"duration":0.26}]},{"speakerName":"Charles E. Whittaker","textObjs":[{"text":"-- purchasing for.","start":3634.818,"stop":3636.114,"duration":1.3}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"To the treasurer of the bar, the association.","start":3636.114,"stop":3641.458,"duration":5.34}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"We'll recess now, Mr. Isaksen.","start":3641.458,"stop":3645.737,"duration":4.28}]}]},{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - January 18, 1961 (Part 2)","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren7/oral_argument_audio/14533","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice, may it please the Court.","start":0,"stop":5.782,"duration":5.78},{"text":"The argument on behalf of the appellee will be divided between myself and the Attorney General of Wisconsin.","start":5.782,"stop":16.103,"duration":10.32},{"text":"And I will try to deal with the questions of jurisdiction and First Amendment freedoms and my associate will discuss the proposition that integration of the Bar is a reasonable form and means of regulating the profession.","start":16.103,"stop":36.946,"duration":20.84},{"text":"With respect to the jurisdictional question of whether an appeal lies in this case under subsection 2 of Section 1257, there is no doubt that the word statute of any state mean legislative action of some kind whether it is direct action by the legislature or -- or by delegated authority to a Commissioner of board or a municipality in the form of municipal ordinances.","start":36.946,"stop":75.44,"duration":38.49},{"text":"Likewise, there is no doubt that the integration orders here in question, orders promulgated by the Wisconsin Supreme Court constitute judicial action.","start":75.44,"stop":89.893,"duration":14.45},{"text":"The only question then, the only possible issue is whether such judicial action can be equated to legislative action under the word statute of any State as it appears in the appeal statute.","start":89.893,"stop":105.955,"duration":16.06},{"text":"And we think clearly not because of the traditional distinction between legislative and judicial functions of the Government which would be obliterated if judicial action was said to be the same for the purposes of the appeal statute as legislative action.","start":105.955,"stop":127.483,"duration":21.53},{"text":"As far as appellant's argument is concerned that if the orders have the effect of law, that is true of all judicial acts.","start":127.483,"stop":138.295,"duration":10.81},{"text":"Orders and judgments of courts have the effect and force of law as in the case of enactments of a legislature that no one would contend that thereby, they are state statutes under subsection 2 of 1257.","start":138.295,"stop":156.102,"duration":17.81},{"text":"If Congress had intended the words statute of any state to apply to judicial action, it certainly as Mr. -- as it has been said by Mr. Justice Brandeis in a dissenting opinion, it could've made its intent and meaning clearer in the wording of the statute.","start":156.102,"stop":180.107,"duration":24}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":180.107,"stop":194.891,"duration":14.78}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"They -- yes, sir.","start":194.891,"stop":195.69,"duration":0.8},{"text":"They were expressed in a dissenting opinion with respect to a different type of action.","start":195.69,"stop":201.773,"duration":6.08}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":201.773,"stop":211.056,"duration":9.28}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":211.056,"stop":212.1,"duration":1.04}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":212.1,"stop":232.507,"duration":20.41}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":232.507,"stop":232.993,"duration":0.49},{"text":"Only that they do not come within the provisions for review under the subsection 2 by appeal.","start":232.993,"stop":241.331,"duration":8.34},{"text":"They should come in under certiorari.","start":241.331,"stop":246.208,"duration":4.88}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"So the matter could be here anyway?","start":246.208,"stop":248.094,"duration":1.89}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":248.094,"stop":248.581,"duration":0.49},{"text":"And that we have pointed out in our briefs.","start":248.581,"stop":250.909,"duration":2.33}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, yes.","start":250.909,"stop":252.712,"duration":1.8}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Now --","start":252.712,"stop":253.8,"duration":1.09}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you have (Inaudible)","start":253.8,"stop":257.091,"duration":3.29}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":257.091,"stop":258.644,"duration":1.55},{"text":"Mr. Justice Clark, we do have a State statute in Wisconsin 256.31, which was enacted in 1943 and which created the State Bar of Wisconsin.","start":258.644,"stop":272.795,"duration":14.15},{"text":"And --","start":272.795,"stop":273.25,"duration":0.45}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":273.25,"stop":276.682,"duration":3.43}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"And the statute directed the Supreme Court to implement it by proper rules, but the Supreme Court of Wisconsin in the first, what I call four integration cases, said that that statute was not binding upon it that integration of the bar was a judicial function and not a legislative function.","start":276.682,"stop":305.373,"duration":28.69},{"text":"And that this statute merely declared the -- was a declaration by the legislature that it would serve the public interest to have an integrated bar.","start":305.373,"stop":318.393,"duration":13.02},{"text":"And the Court thereupon in this first integration case which we have cited several times in our brief declined to integrate the Bar.","start":318.393,"stop":331.081,"duration":12.69},{"text":"Its reason at that time was that there were so many lawyers in the military service that it thought that this matter ought to be deferred.","start":331.081,"stop":339.57,"duration":8.49}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But that (Inaudible)","start":339.57,"stop":364.333,"duration":24.76}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it sounds like --","start":364.333,"stop":365.486,"duration":1.15}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":365.486,"stop":376.577,"duration":11.09}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Mr. -- Mr. Justice Frankfurter.","start":376.577,"stop":378.242,"duration":1.67}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":378.242,"stop":382.063,"duration":3.82}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Correct, sir.","start":382.063,"stop":383.407,"duration":1.34},{"text":"That is precisely what they said in more attack for language.","start":383.407,"stop":387.125,"duration":3.72}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":387.125,"stop":389.226,"duration":2.1}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"They traced --","start":389.226,"stop":389.619,"duration":0.39}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"So that then (Inaudible) to some legislative Government whether a non (Inaudible) of the State or as both specifically come to what of an agency (Inaudible), but if you would say that that Government the legislature couldn't pass that (Inaudible)","start":389.619,"stop":437.626,"duration":48.01}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that should we -- that should we to try to point out in our --","start":437.626,"stop":439.733,"duration":2.11}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":439.733,"stop":454.428,"duration":14.69}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir and we have stated that in our brief in -- in discussing this very jurisdictional question.","start":454.428,"stop":458.907,"duration":4.48}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":458.907,"stop":473.603,"duration":14.7}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"That's --","start":473.603,"stop":473.833,"duration":0.23}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":473.833,"stop":482.152,"duration":8.32}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that -- that is our argument Your Honor.","start":482.152,"stop":485.506,"duration":3.35},{"text":"That this is judicial action and not legislative action because of the very fact that we have had a statute passed here by the Wisconsin legislature creating the State Bar and our Supreme Court said, “No” in a lengthy scholarly opinion reviewing the authority of the Court with respect to the profession and saying, this is our responsibility and not your responsibility.","start":485.506,"stop":509.836,"duration":24.33}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":509.836,"stop":520.282,"duration":10.45}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct, sir.","start":520.282,"stop":522.191,"duration":1.91},{"text":"The alleged statute is merely the Supreme Court said in delicate language, “We appreciate the -- the legislative enactment because it tells us that the legislature of the State of Wisconsin thinks it will serve the public interest.”","start":522.191,"stop":538.519,"duration":16.33}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":538.519,"stop":541.61,"duration":3.09}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, sir.","start":541.61,"stop":547.001,"duration":5.39},{"text":"That opinion is in 244 Wisconsin 8 and the same doctrine is referred to in the subsequent integration cases in Wisconsin.","start":547.001,"stop":563.166,"duration":16.17}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"But the opinion of that case (Inaudible)","start":563.166,"stop":567.379,"duration":4.21}]},{"speakerName":"Leon E. Isaksen","textObjs":[{"text":"This Court?","start":567.379,"stop":568.112,"duration":0.73},{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":568.112,"stop":570.354,"duration":2.24},{"text":"In that connection Your Honor, in 1946, and all this impetus, all this effort to create the State Bar, it's interesting to note, came from the leaders of the voluntary bar association for the obvious reason that they were having trouble and they were ineffectual and unable to do and accomplish the aims and goals they had set forth before them.","start":570.354,"stop":599.712,"duration":29.36},{"text":"In 1946, they came to the Court again and asked that the Bar be integration -- be integrated.","start":599.712,"stop":608.556,"duration":8.84},{"text":"They came at that time with some form of petition signed by a lot of lawyers.","start":608.556,"stop":613.399,"duration":4.84},{"text":"The Court indicated it wasn't interested in what the lawyers felt about integration and it decided not to integrate the Bar.","start":613.399,"stop":624.978,"duration":11.58},{"text":"Then, in 1956, these Bar leaders again petitioned the Court to integrate it.","start":624.978,"stop":634.407,"duration":9.43},{"text":"This time, the Court said, \"Well, it's been tried in a number of States.","start":634.407,"stop":639.907,"duration":5.5},{"text":"We'll try it in Wisconsin for a test period of two years.\"","start":639.907,"stop":648.918,"duration":9.01},{"text":"At the end of that two-year period, the Wisconsin Court reviewed the situation in a very fine opinion in 5 Wisconsin.","start":648.918,"stop":673.048,"duration":24.13},{"text":"2d 618, the Wisconsin Court pointed out that all of the objections that had been raised by integration had not materialized.","start":673.048,"stop":685.911,"duration":12.86},{"text":"None of them had materialized.","start":685.911,"stop":691.856,"duration":5.95},{"text":"It pointed out that under the two-year experiment with integration it had been demonstrated that the integrated bar had increased its services to the profession and had increased its contributions to the administration of justice.","start":691.856,"stop":714.495,"duration":22.64},{"text":"It went on to point out the close relationship in the judicial process between the lawyer and the Courts, but the Courts depend upon the lawyers and their scholarship and their aid in assistance in the functioning of the judicial process in that, it is not undemocratic to require those who are privileged to practice law and are entrusted with the duty to secure or protect the property, rights, and liberties of others to become bound together in a united effort to increase their own capabilities to maintain the high-standards of the group and to increase the effectiveness of their service to the public.","start":714.495,"stop":764.002,"duration":49.51},{"text":"The integrated bar said it has been defined as a process by which every member of the Bar is given an opportunity to do his share in carrying out the public service of the Bar and oblige to bear his portion of the responsibility.","start":764.002,"stop":779.778,"duration":15.78},{"text":"And it added, most objections have centered round the obligation to bear a portion of the responsibility, but in the nature of things, every privilege has a correlative obligation.","start":779.778,"stop":799.523,"duration":19.75},{"text":"Now, the counsel for the appellant here has stated that in the opinion of the court below that the Court justified or grounded the need for integration on the basis of the public be entitled to the views of the lawyers and legislative matters.","start":799.523,"stop":834.955,"duration":35.43},{"text":"Now, I think that that gives undue emphasis to the State and the Court, but the Court merely said in that case was that appellant's argument as to unconstitutionality is grounded upon the proposition that the State Bar expresses opinions on legislative matters.","start":834.955,"stop":857.946,"duration":22.99},{"text":"And then it went on to say that this was a -- this serve the public purpose, that this was in the public interest and that the public was entitled to know it how these experts what their opinions were on legislative matters within a narrow restricted field.","start":857.946,"stop":879.24,"duration":21.29}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"May I ask you, next to the argument that you made, you probably going to jurisdictional argument, what issues (Inaudible)","start":879.24,"stop":893.795,"duration":14.55}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Sir, I think that this case presents with respect to the integrated bar really only the issue decided in Hanson with respect to labor organizations namely the question whether lawyers can be compelled to belong and pay dues to the State Bar in the exercise of the State's power to regulate the Bar.","start":893.795,"stop":922.547,"duration":28.75},{"text":"Appellant has made it clear here and it certainly clear from his complaint and from the record that his objection as to the general proposition of having to belong to the Bar.","start":922.547,"stop":939.53,"duration":16.98},{"text":"His second objection is to the Bar rendering any legislative services, giving any legislative opinions regardless of whether he agrees or disagrees.","start":939.53,"stop":952.056,"duration":12.53},{"text":"In fact, in his complaint, he doesn't allege any disagreement except in one instance.","start":952.056,"stop":959.044,"duration":6.99},{"text":"He says that the State Bar opposed some legislation which he favored but he doesn't say what it is, but going through the few bills up to the time of the complaint, and going through the few bills in which the State Bar took the position in the period of a two and a half years of its existence there were about 13 or 14 bills on which the State Bar took a position.","start":959.044,"stop":991.528,"duration":32.48},{"text":"The only bill which he had opposed that I can see during that time is the bill to repeal the Integrated Bar Act and the position that we took on that was merely to write a letter to the Assembly Judiciary Committee which I wrote merely stating that under the decisions of the Wisconsin Supreme Court, the responsibility for continuing or discontinuing integration was with it as a matter of law and not with the legislature and that its repeal would be ineffective for the purpose of disintegrating the State Bar.","start":991.528,"stop":1034.772,"duration":43.24}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1034.772,"stop":1044.217,"duration":9.45}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":1044.217,"stop":1044.761,"duration":0.54}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But in (Inaudible) any difference -- if this appeal (Inaudible)","start":1044.761,"stop":1058.763,"duration":14}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think so, Your Honor.","start":1058.763,"stop":1064.084,"duration":5.32},{"text":"So, we have these general contentions.","start":1064.084,"stop":1069.346,"duration":5.26},{"text":"He hasn't shown how he has been hurt or injured.","start":1069.346,"stop":1074.679,"duration":5.33},{"text":"His contention is, even if I agree with every view expressed by the State Bar, as a constitutional matter, you can express views.","start":1074.679,"stop":1086.481,"duration":11.8},{"text":"Now first, as to his contention, that his freedom of association is violated by being required to be a member of the integrated bar.","start":1086.481,"stop":1099.256,"duration":12.78},{"text":"As to that, his objection is the same as in Hanson bear membership is a ground for his objection.","start":1099.256,"stop":1112.783,"duration":13.53},{"text":"As he stated here, he admits the power of the State to require a license fee of lawyers for regulatory purposes.","start":1112.783,"stop":1124.095,"duration":11.31},{"text":"So, his objection is not to the annual dues.","start":1124.095,"stop":1127.156,"duration":3.06},{"text":"His objection runs to being compelled to belong to an organization of lawyers.","start":1127.156,"stop":1138.939,"duration":11.78},{"text":"But he was required to belong to the bar before integration when he of his own free will decided to become a lawyer and qualify himself to become a lawyer, he had to be admitted to the Bar, he had to become a member of that Bar and in order to practice law, he had to remain a member in good standing.","start":1138.939,"stop":1161.99,"duration":23.05},{"text":"And as such a member, he accepted all the conditions and burdens and restraints which go at the pre -- prerogatives.","start":1161.99,"stop":1169.683,"duration":7.69}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"So to speak, he have the lawyers or pay for it.","start":1169.683,"stop":1175.859,"duration":6.18}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"He didn't have to pay for it Your Honor but he certainly could as a matter of constitutional principle be compelled to pay a license fee for regulation.","start":1175.859,"stop":1188.552,"duration":12.69}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"He didn't object to that (Inaudible)","start":1188.552,"stop":1190.141,"duration":1.59}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"He didn't object to that.","start":1190.141,"stop":1192.978,"duration":2.84},{"text":"But, with respect to association, he isn't compelled now to associate with anybody anymore than before integration.","start":1192.978,"stop":1200.406,"duration":7.43},{"text":"He doesn't have to attend a single one of the meetings of the Bar.","start":1200.406,"stop":1205.05,"duration":4.64},{"text":"If he wants to forego the benefits of those meetings, he is a free citizen to forego then.","start":1205.05,"stop":1211.462,"duration":6.41},{"text":"He doesn't have to associate with anybody.","start":1211.462,"stop":1213.228,"duration":1.77},{"text":"He doesn't have to vote in any elections we have under the State Bar rules, a democratic self governing form of organization with the right which includes every single lawyer in the State and there is no distinction as to class or creed, religion or race.","start":1213.228,"stop":1236.469,"duration":23.24},{"text":"It represents everybody and everybody is given an opportunity to vote.","start":1236.469,"stop":1240.714,"duration":4.24},{"text":"Everybody is given an opportunity to make his voice heard in the self-government of this organization, but he was compelled before integration to submit the certain restraints.","start":1240.714,"stop":1259.845,"duration":19.13},{"text":"As a lawyer, he does not have the full freedom of any other citizen.","start":1259.845,"stop":1268.251,"duration":8.41},{"text":"He is subject to the control and the discipline and the supervision of the Court because he is a part of that primary function of Government, the administration of justice.","start":1268.251,"stop":1280.983,"duration":12.73},{"text":"He, the lawyer is the moving and advising officer of the Court and as such, he is always subject to the discipline and the regulation of the Court.","start":1280.983,"stop":1295.416,"duration":14.43},{"text":"What integration did was simply to take this body of court officers, called the Bar, and give it a constitution in the form of rules and bylaws under which the profession could operate with the form of self-government.","start":1295.416,"stop":1314.786,"duration":19.37},{"text":"All was subject to the continuing supervision of the Court and the Court has said in these integration cases, they said in this case the court below and in 5 Wisconsin, “We stand here ready to take any remedial action if the integrated bar should abuse its powers or step beyond the lines we had delineated or otherwise, do anything which is not in keeping with the public purposes which the integrated bar is suppose to serve.”","start":1314.786,"stop":1360.28,"duration":45.49},{"text":"But the Supreme --","start":1360.28,"stop":1360.594,"duration":0.31}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible) with respect of controlling what they say and do and that then the limits of that charter that he spoke of as I understood the counsel to the Supreme Court made in the charter stating what the -- the jurisdiction was.","start":1360.594,"stop":1384.742,"duration":24.15},{"text":"Now, if they stay within that jurisdiction, he's representing the opinions of the public, matters of the quasi political let us say, the Supreme Court deserve the right to strike that down and say you cannot do this or -- or do they have other autonomy that they can do what they want within that charter?","start":1384.742,"stop":1406.269,"duration":21.53}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, they are autonomous and the Supreme Court has pointed out in 5 Wisconsin.","start":1406.269,"stop":1413.478,"duration":7.21},{"text":"that we will not be a censor of the Bar as long as they stay within the limits that we have marked out in these rules and bylaws.","start":1413.478,"stop":1421.963,"duration":8.48},{"text":"We believe in an independent Bar and we want to foster this idea of independence, but the integrated bar is for -- is to serve public purposes -- public interest.","start":1421.963,"stop":1437.546,"duration":15.58}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"And the majority determines what the public interest is?","start":1437.546,"stop":1440.395,"duration":2.85}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"And the majority determines questions of self-government within --","start":1440.395,"stop":1445.019,"duration":4.62}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Not necessarily self-government, the question is what is the difference when you get to things that are fairly involved or some essential -- let's say the law of corporation which points out (Inaudible) changes in the law of corporation.","start":1445.019,"stop":1462.961,"duration":17.94},{"text":"You don't consider that a matter of organization.","start":1462.961,"stop":1466.364,"duration":3.4}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":1466.364,"stop":1466.816,"duration":0.45},{"text":"We don't.","start":1466.816,"stop":1467.849,"duration":1.03}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible) they're doing something of that (Inaudible)","start":1467.849,"stop":1472.147,"duration":4.3}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"The Board of Governors of the Executive Committee is given a discretion and judgment to decide what view to take on such matters, but when it comes to the question of corporations, the question would be whether it is within the narrow confines of what the Court has said we can't take positions of.","start":1472.147,"stop":1492.588,"duration":20.44},{"text":"The Court has limited us strictly to administration of justice, the Court reforms, practice and procedure.","start":1492.588,"stop":1502.447,"duration":9.86}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I wish your counsel said that they haven't (Inaudible) in the lower court.","start":1502.447,"stop":1508.416,"duration":5.97}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"They -- these sections -- the sections you see that in the Bar as you undoubtedly know, there are number of committees and a number of sections.","start":1508.416,"stop":1517.734,"duration":9.32},{"text":"There is a section that deals with corporate law.","start":1517.734,"stop":1520.697,"duration":2.96},{"text":"They study corporate law.","start":1520.697,"stop":1522.36,"duration":1.66},{"text":"There is a section on taxation.","start":1522.36,"stop":1524.296,"duration":1.94},{"text":"They study questions of taxation.","start":1524.296,"stop":1526.466,"duration":2.17}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Insurance and negligence --","start":1526.466,"stop":1527.38,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Insurance and negligence and family law labor relations and so forth, but that studying these things having forums, having discussions on the problems and on the meanings of the laws and the decisions as they come down, there's quite a different matter from taking a position on the legislative measure.","start":1527.38,"stop":1551.523,"duration":24.14}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, do they not take position of any of those matters?","start":1551.523,"stop":1555.703,"duration":4.18}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"They do not take positions on any of those matters except and unless they relate to the administration of justice, practice and procedure.","start":1555.703,"stop":1565.574,"duration":9.87}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1565.574,"stop":1595.142,"duration":29.57}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":1595.142,"stop":1595.6,"duration":0.46},{"text":"The Court in this case said we couldn't do that.","start":1595.6,"stop":1598.249,"duration":2.65},{"text":"The Court said that we have to stay within these limits and that -- in that respect, we are different from the American Bar Association or the Bar Association you just mentioned.","start":1598.249,"stop":1607.819,"duration":9.57}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But these things -- does that mean workings of the Court?","start":1607.819,"stop":1611.948,"duration":4.13}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"The workings of the Court.","start":1611.948,"stop":1613.161,"duration":1.21},{"text":"They are just --","start":1613.161,"stop":1613.445,"duration":0.28}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"It's something you should have before?","start":1613.445,"stop":1615.126,"duration":1.68},{"text":"What's the matter for?","start":1615.126,"stop":1617.196,"duration":2.07}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I'm not sure that I could --","start":1617.196,"stop":1618.567,"duration":1.37}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1618.567,"stop":1622.99,"duration":4.42}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"I think we have been unduly limited.","start":1622.99,"stop":1625.357,"duration":2.37}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I thought you said you just -- you just preserved the independence of the Bar?","start":1625.357,"stop":1630.502,"duration":5.14}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"But, they have preserved the independence on the Bar but on legislative matters, they have limited the Bar to these narrow fields apparently with the thought of keeping us out of the political sphere.","start":1630.502,"stop":1644.47,"duration":13.97}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Not with the (Inaudible)","start":1644.47,"stop":1655.512,"duration":11.04}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":1655.512,"stop":1655.905,"duration":0.39},{"text":"I think they can.","start":1655.905,"stop":1657.016,"duration":1.11}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What's that (Inaudible)","start":1657.016,"stop":1659.033,"duration":2.02}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"I would think that that would come under administration of justice.","start":1659.033,"stop":1664.054,"duration":5.02}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1664.054,"stop":1681.72,"duration":17.67}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"I would say so, sir.","start":1681.72,"stop":1682.49,"duration":0.77}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1682.49,"stop":1683.824,"duration":1.33}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"I would say that wasn't.","start":1683.824,"stop":1685.351,"duration":1.53}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And (Inaudible)","start":1685.351,"stop":1693.188,"duration":7.84}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":1693.188,"stop":1694.16,"duration":0.97}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1694.16,"stop":1700.359,"duration":6.2}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Your Honor, up to now in four years of integration, we have taken positions on I think 19 or 20 measures, so that there hasn't been any problem.","start":1700.359,"stop":1712.986,"duration":12.63}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible) people?","start":1712.986,"stop":1715.735,"duration":2.75}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Well -- where -- where a young growing integrated bar.","start":1715.735,"stop":1720.451,"duration":4.72}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Was it in a short time to have these policies and all of that?","start":1720.451,"stop":1724.637,"duration":4.19}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I think that we should be permitted Your Honor to go further than the narrow limits that the Court has laid out for us, but we should stay out of matters which are political.","start":1724.637,"stop":1739.339,"duration":14.7}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"It sounds to me if I may say so that your -- the way you fix the Bar, it sounds very much like the old NRA where the Congress gave businessmen not lawyers, businessmen without a need fixed the side of the policy has on it and then that it was submitted to whatever governmental agency was there, they might approve it or might not.","start":1739.339,"stop":1766.602,"duration":27.26},{"text":"You submit yours to the Court and that is the difference between a delegation of power in the NRA and delegation of power here --","start":1766.602,"stop":1778.946,"duration":12.34}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"We do not submit our legislative proposals to the Court.","start":1778.946,"stop":1784.66,"duration":5.71},{"text":"The Board of Governors --","start":1784.66,"stop":1786.746,"duration":2.09}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the question I was getting at was this.","start":1786.746,"stop":1788.97,"duration":2.22},{"text":"It seems to be that in both of these cases, other groups like this, the question ultimately gets down to whether the Government has the power to divide citizens into groups or segments according to, we'll say vocations or professions or what not, somehow and provide that all of them have pay funds to run their association and that it can propagandize for the views if the majority approved.","start":1788.97,"stop":1819.31,"duration":30.34},{"text":"Is that an unfair statement of it?","start":1819.31,"stop":1821.11,"duration":1.8}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I don't think that in the case of the legislative measures of --","start":1821.11,"stop":1824.501,"duration":3.39}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Maybe right.","start":1824.501,"stop":1825.148,"duration":0.65},{"text":"I'm not familiar -- I don't see --","start":1825.148,"stop":1826.253,"duration":1.11}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think it's propaganda, but I do think that the idea of giving a group that is subject to regulation and that has particularly heavy public duties, the opportunity for self-government is a good one.","start":1826.253,"stop":1849.972,"duration":23.72}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"We have self-government -- we have self-government in this country because we have a Government, but can Congress delegate a legislative body that -- I -- I have a hard time speaking of it as self-government is a kind that the country had, say to divide groups and let the Government require them to pay money into that and they make laws which of a propagate ideas which are binding on the minority.","start":1849.972,"stop":1881.768,"duration":31.8},{"text":"I understand that for the Government, but I don't quite understand that the --","start":1881.768,"stop":1886.844,"duration":5.08}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, if it's correct for the Government then you have it happening all the time, in all different levels of government, taking positions on legislative matter and even lobbying and I can say to all kinds of even the judicial conference of the United States makes legislative recommendations.","start":1886.844,"stop":1905.13,"duration":18.29},{"text":"Now --","start":1905.13,"stop":1905.407,"duration":0.28}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"The basic difference -- excuse me.","start":1905.407,"stop":1906.661,"duration":1.25}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1906.661,"stop":1908.824,"duration":2.16}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"The integrated bar is a governmental agency too.","start":1908.824,"stop":1911.637,"duration":2.81}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Is that -- do that, no one is compelled to the (Inaudible)","start":1911.637,"stop":1918.244,"duration":6.61}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"But, public funds are being used to support this effort.","start":1918.244,"stop":1922.817,"duration":4.57}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I don't -- I don't think the counsel objected to the regulation that (Inaudible) do you think -- do you think was that a reason for (Inaudible) medical profession held belong in the organization and pay dues and what the power of the majority (Inaudible)","start":1922.817,"stop":1957.915,"duration":35.1}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"I agree that -- I think that that would be constitutional and valid in the case --","start":1957.915,"stop":1961.812,"duration":3.9}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you think that that inducts preference?","start":1961.812,"stop":1966.211,"duration":4.4}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not so sure about that.","start":1966.211,"stop":1969.222,"duration":3.01}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Why not?","start":1969.222,"stop":1969.701,"duration":0.48}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Because I think that -- I think that it maybe constitutional in the case of commerce but I have a little more difficulty because the medical profession has a much greater public service -- public interest served.","start":1969.701,"stop":1986.917,"duration":17.22}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Why didn't you say that?","start":1986.917,"stop":1988.721,"duration":1.8}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Health, life and death --","start":1988.721,"stop":1989.385,"duration":0.66}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you have a plumbing lady?","start":1989.385,"stop":1991.157,"duration":1.77}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"[Attempt to Laughter] Yes, I have.","start":1991.157,"stop":1993.121,"duration":1.96}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Is plumbing then to a part of public health and safety?","start":1993.121,"stop":2000.229,"duration":7.11}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"It might be that -- that the plumbers too could be regulated in that fashion.","start":2000.229,"stop":2006.269,"duration":6.04}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"How can you -- how can you draw a way by which (Inaudible)","start":2006.269,"stop":2046.592,"duration":40.32}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"We held in that case that it didn't violate the equal protection law, that was the --","start":2046.592,"stop":2051.121,"duration":4.53}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2051.121,"stop":2051.551,"duration":0.43}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"At least that's -- at least that's what I thought when I wrote the opinion?","start":2051.551,"stop":2055.192,"duration":3.64}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2055.192,"stop":2064.695,"duration":9.5}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible) that question after, I don't have the full authority to say the State Bar for many years to take part with the simple statement (Inaudible).","start":2064.695,"stop":2080.804,"duration":16.11},{"text":"What I'm trying to do in my mind (Inaudible) between this case and the basis of this proceeding and finding that there's a little difference in my mind at the present time and which I believe that some of these activities that we're talking about in the two cases are very much alike.","start":2080.804,"stop":2107.46,"duration":26.66},{"text":"And I have to put a little help to see if there -- if there is any differentiation between -- insofar as the First Amendment is concerned, insofar as the right of association and not to association is concerned.","start":2107.46,"stop":2129.509,"duration":22.05},{"text":"If there is any differentiation, I'd like to know.","start":2129.509,"stop":2132.938,"duration":3.43},{"text":"That -- that's the reason why I ask you these questions (Inaudible)","start":2132.938,"stop":2139.236,"duration":6.3}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Your Honor, I don't think there is any differentiation between Hanson in this case on the proposition of freedom of association.","start":2139.236,"stop":2146.682,"duration":7.45},{"text":"I think the principle established in Hanson as far as freedom of association is concerned applies to this case too although of course the Bar is different than a labor union.","start":2146.682,"stop":2160.776,"duration":14.09}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"If the constitutionally there?","start":2160.776,"stop":2163.378,"duration":2.6}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, although -- I mean, in make up, but I think the constitutional principle applies that if you can compel persons to belong to a labor union in the interest of the legitimate governmental objective of maintaining industrial peace along the arteries of commerce, you certainly should be able to compel lawyers to belong to a Bar organization in the interest of improving the profession in regulating a profession and improving and promoting the administration of justice.","start":2163.378,"stop":2197.919,"duration":34.54}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"But I -- I would agree on the same principles say we're, if they both were engaged in the same types of activities (Inaudible) personal facts of constitutionality is the same in both instances?","start":2197.919,"stop":2215.635,"duration":17.72}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir, but I do think there is a difference here between our case and the case of Street in that we do not support any political or judicial candidates, we do not engage in any ideological, political partisan activity of any kind.","start":2215.635,"stop":2240.885,"duration":25.25}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, in that case, he may object to all the legislative factors as being beyond the scope because it abridged the right of the plaintiffs in that case to -- to associate and to speak.","start":2240.885,"stop":2252.912,"duration":12.03},{"text":"And that in a sense, we say it's the same taken under the number of judgments in the county.","start":2252.912,"stop":2268.709,"duration":15.8},{"text":"That's rather a political thing that amounts to and quite and also the question of how much judges should be paid is more or less a political thing and I would think just as much as a minimum wage law, but in that case, they contended that the fact should then go beyond the -- the right to impose on the proponents.","start":2268.709,"stop":2302.748,"duration":34.04}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, when you deal with subjects that are in these loaded fields which the Court has marked out in this case, Your Honor, there maybe some political aspects to them or to some of them, but in the main, they are technical, noncontroversial items of legislation in which the lawyer certainly ought to take a part.","start":2302.748,"stop":2333.36,"duration":30.61},{"text":"I think the Bar has been --","start":2333.36,"stop":2335.013,"duration":1.65}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"He should be compelled to take a part, shouldn't he?","start":2335.013,"stop":2339.246,"duration":4.23}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, they're not compelled to take a part.","start":2339.246,"stop":2340.925,"duration":1.68},{"text":"They're --","start":2340.925,"stop":2341.117,"duration":0.19}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well then, you said you know they should take a part.","start":2341.117,"stop":2343.326,"duration":2.21}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2343.326,"stop":2344.275,"duration":0.95}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"You are talking about association, and you haven't yet discussed the question of the collection of money, getting money for the purpose of using it to take part in view of what is the political activity.","start":2344.275,"stop":2358.093,"duration":13.82}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think they --","start":2358.093,"stop":2358.391,"duration":0.3}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"They knew the passage of legislature.","start":2358.391,"stop":2360.354,"duration":1.96}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think they are political activities.","start":2360.354,"stop":2363.236,"duration":2.88},{"text":"And in --","start":2363.236,"stop":2363.887,"duration":0.65}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, they are activities in connection of the statute of the legislation on which people differ, on which they frequently have some of the biggest fights they ever had.","start":2363.887,"stop":2372.587,"duration":8.7},{"text":"How many judges do you have?","start":2372.587,"stop":2373.839,"duration":1.25},{"text":"What are you going to pay them?","start":2373.839,"stop":2375.285,"duration":1.45}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"But other public agencies are taking --","start":2375.285,"stop":2376.935,"duration":1.65}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I mean, do they have a referendums or --","start":2376.935,"stop":2378.877,"duration":1.94}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Other public agencies are taking positions on legislation all the time.","start":2378.877,"stop":2383.042,"duration":4.16}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2383.042,"stop":2410.817,"duration":27.78}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct Your Honor.","start":2410.817,"stop":2411.822,"duration":1.01}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, suppose (Inaudible)","start":2411.822,"stop":2443.175,"duration":31.35}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"I would say that that was within the sphere of the administration of justice.","start":2443.175,"stop":2446.39,"duration":3.21}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you think that it can all (Inaudible)?","start":2446.39,"stop":2449.315,"duration":2.93}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":2449.315,"stop":2449.722,"duration":0.41},{"text":"I can think of a lot more political --","start":2449.722,"stop":2451.054,"duration":1.33}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2451.054,"stop":2460.995,"duration":9.94}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"It -- it certainly has political --","start":2460.995,"stop":2462.107,"duration":1.11}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2462.107,"stop":2478.491,"duration":16.38}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, I do.","start":2478.491,"stop":2479.148,"duration":0.66}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2479.148,"stop":2480.512,"duration":1.36}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, I do, sir.","start":2480.512,"stop":2481.131,"duration":0.62}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2481.131,"stop":2484.439,"duration":3.31}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, I do.","start":2484.439,"stop":2485.286,"duration":0.85},{"text":"But --","start":2485.286,"stop":2485.667,"duration":0.38}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2485.667,"stop":2509.756,"duration":24.09}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I am not so -- this term political means many things and we don't seem to be concerned -- we don't seem to be concern with all of the departments of Government who --","start":2509.756,"stop":2524.917,"duration":15.16}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2524.917,"stop":2563.537,"duration":38.62}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"My time is up and my associate will now take over.","start":2563.537,"stop":2566.495,"duration":2.96}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"You have to answer an important question that Justice Frankfurter has asked of the counsel.","start":2566.495,"stop":2572.403,"duration":5.91},{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2572.403,"stop":2580.256,"duration":7.85}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"The State Bar, Your Honor, furnishes an annual report to the Supreme Court, a financial report.","start":2580.256,"stop":2586.809,"duration":6.55}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Just a financial report?","start":2586.809,"stop":2587.808,"duration":1}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Just a financial report and I might say that there is continuing supervision here in that officers of the State Bar meet with the Court from time to time to go over their affairs, so it isn't a thing that isn't a case of there being just out here and left alone to without any guidance.","start":2587.808,"stop":2605.859,"duration":18.05}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":2605.859,"stop":2606.579,"duration":0.72},{"text":"no, it wasn't for that purpose.","start":2606.579,"stop":2608.81,"duration":2.23},{"text":"The important purpose is that to ascertain just what the appellees State Bar covered in governing apparently to the Court show what the activities of the State Bar (Inaudible)","start":2608.81,"stop":2626.994,"duration":18.18}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't have such a report.","start":2626.994,"stop":2629.405,"duration":2.41},{"text":"We might be able to find something that would be in the nature of such -- which should give such information.","start":2629.405,"stop":2635.483,"duration":6.08}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"You don't quite (Inaudible)","start":2635.483,"stop":2638.45,"duration":2.97}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":2638.45,"stop":2639.177,"duration":0.73},{"text":"We don't.","start":2639.177,"stop":2639.561,"duration":0.38},{"text":"We did make a report to the Wisconsin Supreme Court in 1958 when the integration was considered as to whether it shall be continued.","start":2639.561,"stop":2647.817,"duration":8.26}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2647.817,"stop":2668.243,"duration":20.43}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, we sent out --","start":2668.243,"stop":2669.098,"duration":0.86}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2669.098,"stop":2672.399,"duration":3.3}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir.","start":2672.399,"stop":2672.77,"duration":0.37},{"text":"We have not sent out any particular questions.","start":2672.77,"stop":2675.105,"duration":2.34},{"text":"The only ballot we sent out is written out of ballot it's a -- what it is in the sense a questionnaire each year when the dues statements are sent out a -- statement is sent out asking the members of the Bar to suggest any changes in the rule of bylaws and activities or any improvements that could be made.","start":2675.105,"stop":2699.087,"duration":23.98},{"text":"That's the only sort of thing to do.","start":2699.087,"stop":2700.385,"duration":1.3},{"text":"I would like to comment on one more thing that was --","start":2700.385,"stop":2703.196,"duration":2.81}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Before you get to that (Inaudible)","start":2703.196,"stop":2714.488,"duration":11.29}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":2714.488,"stop":2714.892,"duration":0.4},{"text":"We will do that.","start":2714.892,"stop":2716.697,"duration":1.81},{"text":"On this question of discipline, a statement was made here by counsel that our disciplinary procedure is the same under the integrated bar as it was under the voluntary bar and I just beg to differ with them that we have an entirely different procedure under the full voluntary bar.","start":2716.697,"stop":2736.232,"duration":19.53},{"text":"We really didn't have any grievance procedure.","start":2736.232,"stop":2740.09,"duration":3.86},{"text":"We had a little grievance committee and that it would pass the complaints on to the local bar associations and more serious ones would go up to the State Board of Bar commissioners.","start":2740.09,"stop":2752.618,"duration":12.53},{"text":"Now, we have a very extensive set up whereby the State is divided into nine districts and there are grievance committees of at least five lawyers in each district where a regular procedure that they follow for handling these things and for investigating them and for holding hearings and for passing on their recommendations.","start":2752.618,"stop":2779.704,"duration":27.09},{"text":"They also have the right to investigate misconduct -- judicial misconduct I noticed in the rules.","start":2779.704,"stop":2786.736,"duration":7.03},{"text":"They also have the function and duty of investigating the reinstatement of disbarred or suspended lawyers who are petitioning for reinstatement and make recommendations to the Board of Bar Governors and to the Supreme Court with respect to those things.","start":2786.736,"stop":2804.487,"duration":17.75},{"text":"And I think that the report will show that within the last year and quarter or so, last two years I think it is, they handled around 232 grievance complaints as against 17 that were handled in the year before integration and eight that were handled in the second year before integration.","start":2804.487,"stop":2827.904,"duration":23.42},{"text":"I just want to point out that this had been due to the fact that when you got price and much money, you can do a lot of things you can employ personnel.","start":2827.904,"stop":2834.818,"duration":6.91},{"text":"They have a paid investigator who is full time working on investigation of grievances, the unauthorized practice of the law and assisting the professional ethics committee in interpreting its rules.","start":2834.818,"stop":2849.256,"duration":14.44}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I hadn't understood.","start":2849.256,"stop":2850.257,"duration":1},{"text":"Maybe I -- I'm interested as to prove is the attack based with any extent on the facts the Bar I think decided disciplinary (Inaudible).","start":2850.257,"stop":2861.351,"duration":11.09},{"text":"I can see where it could be charged.","start":2861.351,"stop":2865.069,"duration":3.72},{"text":"Was it good enough that violated some of the constitution?","start":2865.069,"stop":2868.673,"duration":3.6},{"text":"But I haven't understood that would --","start":2868.673,"stop":2870.34,"duration":1.67}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"No, that is not involved, sir.","start":2870.34,"stop":2871.745,"duration":1.4},{"text":"Because the Supreme Courts still retains the power on due hearing and notice to decide disbarment and suspension cases.","start":2871.745,"stop":2880.583,"duration":8.84}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2880.583,"stop":2889.088,"duration":8.51}]},{"speakerName":"Gordon Sinykin","textObjs":[{"text":"Up to now, it doesn't.","start":2889.088,"stop":2890.416,"duration":1.33},{"text":"No sir.","start":2890.416,"stop":2891.788,"duration":1.37},{"text":"It hasn't entered in that field.","start":2891.788,"stop":2903.729,"duration":11.94}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Attorney General Reynolds.","start":2903.729,"stop":2905.386,"duration":1.66}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice and members of the Court.","start":2905.386,"stop":2908.131,"duration":2.74},{"text":"In the next few moments, I would like to address myself to the issue of the -- whether or not the regulations of the Court to the integrated bar and in the State of Wisconsin violates the Fourteenth Amendment.","start":2908.131,"stop":2922.725,"duration":14.59},{"text":"We believe that the regulation is reasonable.","start":2922.725,"stop":2926.611,"duration":3.89},{"text":"The points I would like to discuss at the authority of the Court and briefly, I don't know if we have that in throughout the history of the -- this integrated bar in Wisconsin and the record.","start":2926.611,"stop":2939.825,"duration":13.21},{"text":"The integration of the State Bar of the State of Wisconsin we believe is a reasonable method of regulating the practice of the law.","start":2939.825,"stop":2952.379,"duration":12.55},{"text":"I think that it is quite clear from the pronouncements of this Court and on the history of jurisprudence that the Courts have an obligation to control the practice of law.","start":2952.379,"stop":2965.942,"duration":13.56},{"text":"In England, they did it through the courts, didn't do it but the ends of Court did it, and this Court in several cases has been pointed out such as in the Thread case by Justice Frankfurter, the Court's control over a lawyer's professional life derives from his relation to the responsibilities of the Court.","start":2965.942,"stop":2986.679,"duration":20.74},{"text":"In our briefs, we have cited several other authorities for this.","start":2986.679,"stop":2991.143,"duration":4.46},{"text":"This has been recognized in the State of Wisconsin in our four integration cases where the Supreme Court of our State has indicated that they have a -- they have a responsibility to the practice of law.","start":2991.143,"stop":3007.357,"duration":16.21},{"text":"The -- in addition to that, our state legislature passed the law Section 256.30 which stated as a misdemeanor can practice law without a license and furthermore that you could be held in contempt of Court can practice law without a license which infer -- which indicates the legislature recognized the inherent power of the Court to control the practice of law.","start":3007.357,"stop":3036.528,"duration":29.17}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"That law is enforced at present time.","start":3036.528,"stop":3038.337,"duration":1.81}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"That law is enforced at present time.","start":3038.337,"stop":3040.93,"duration":2.59},{"text":"I think that of course it's not only based on historical precedent but it's based upon practical necessity.","start":3040.93,"stop":3046.894,"duration":5.96},{"text":"It starts out with the practice of law when you are admitted to the Bar, and you are given a monopoly over a certain field of activity and this monopoly, like all monopolies, I believe, have to regulated or at least to this public has to be protected from the abuse of the people who control the monopoly.","start":3046.894,"stop":3066.271,"duration":19.38},{"text":"The Court in Wisconsin felt that it was very important that the Bar association, or the lawyers of the State be conscious of their responsibility to the Court in the administration of justice and to society.","start":3066.271,"stop":3084.894,"duration":18.62},{"text":"In other words, that we rise above mediocrity and the history of the integrated bar in Wisconsin I think indicates that this is a reasonable approach and it has not been something that's rash.","start":3084.894,"stop":3103.056,"duration":18.16},{"text":"Now I'd like to just quickly go through the history.","start":3103.056,"stop":3106.107,"duration":3.05},{"text":"In 1935, the State Legislature of the State of Wisconsin passed a law authorizing the Court to establish the integrated bar.","start":3106.107,"stop":3116.969,"duration":10.86},{"text":"This law was vetoed by the acting governor at the time.","start":3116.969,"stop":3121.702,"duration":4.73},{"text":"In 1943, the state legislature, that is the people of Wisconsin through their legislature, passed another law and directing the Court to integrate the Bar.","start":3121.702,"stop":3133.499,"duration":11.8},{"text":"And to the end, and I quote from the statute “that such association shall promote the public interest by maintaining high standards of conduct in the legal profession and by aiding in the efficient administration of justice”.","start":3133.499,"stop":3146.944,"duration":13.45},{"text":"In other words, the people of the State of Wisconsin were literally crying out to their Court, \"Why don't you supervise these lawyers?\"","start":3146.944,"stop":3155.124,"duration":8.18},{"text":"And the leading members of the Bar also cried out to the Court for that and their cries fell fortunately on deaf ears.","start":3155.124,"stop":3163.188,"duration":8.06},{"text":"In 1946, the Court again refused to integrate the Bar and on the theory to quote them, that the price and I quote is the 46 decision, the phrase of integration that is supervision or policing by the Court by the activities of lawyers and it would be much greater than the Court or any lawyer ought to be willing to pay.","start":3163.188,"stop":3188.101,"duration":24.91},{"text":"That was the logic of the 46 decision.","start":3188.101,"stop":3190.834,"duration":2.73},{"text":"In my judgment, I think the Court misconceived its role because actually, the fact that you have a Laissez-Faire system doesn't mean that you necessarily have -- have freedom.","start":3190.834,"stop":3202.565,"duration":11.73},{"text":"I think the Court has an obligation and they seem to recognize that to prevent things from happening.","start":3202.565,"stop":3209.398,"duration":6.83},{"text":"In 1956, the Court ordered the integration of the Bar on the theory that they are -- that the lawyers are entitled to the supervision and control of the Court.","start":3209.398,"stop":3221.34,"duration":11.94},{"text":"This Court here sitting here today admitted a group of lawyers to the Bar of the United States Supreme Court, you did this on the assumption that the States are assuming their responsibilities to supervise these lawyers.","start":3221.34,"stop":3235.133,"duration":13.79},{"text":"They see to it the lawyers are following the -- the ethics of the profession by carrying out their duties.","start":3235.133,"stop":3243.139,"duration":8.01},{"text":"I think that the record in this case in the case that there have been no violations of any of the freedoms of the appellant is, and there has been no violation of his freedom of speech or his freedom of association.","start":3243.139,"stop":3257.971,"duration":14.83},{"text":"The appellant as my colleague, Mr. Sinykin pointed out the appellant when he became a lawyer, he joined the Bar of the Court.","start":3257.971,"stop":3266.557,"duration":8.59},{"text":"And the integrated bar is merely a mechanism for the Court to supervise its own Bar.","start":3266.557,"stop":3273.373,"duration":6.82},{"text":"And it's up to the State to determine which method of supervision, granting they have the authority to supervise it and it's reasonable as to which method they -- they should use.","start":3273.373,"stop":3286.162,"duration":12.79}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":3286.162,"stop":3295.678,"duration":9.52}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"The -- the State I believe that -- yes.","start":3295.678,"stop":3299.927,"duration":4.25},{"text":"I think the same thing could be said.","start":3299.927,"stop":3301.252,"duration":1.32},{"text":"In other words, the -- the Court is still having integrated bar could have very easily said we will set up a commission and the commission will police the activities.","start":3301.252,"stop":3309.691,"duration":8.44}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"That's -- that's a different thing.","start":3309.691,"stop":3312.205,"duration":2.51},{"text":"That's a different thing to set up a commission to regulate.","start":3312.205,"stop":3316.13,"duration":3.93},{"text":"What I mean is, could they -- with any of the added professions do exactly as they did here, say that anyone in order to -- to be -- to practice that profession in the State must belong to an organization of -- of that profession?","start":3316.13,"stop":3334.625,"duration":18.49}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"It is my opinion that this could only be done provided that there is a State agency that represents the whole State or society at large such as the Court or some other agency appointed by the governor to supervise the -- say the integrated medical profession.","start":3334.625,"stop":3350.158,"duration":15.53}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, supervision in itself relieved any disabilities because of constitutional defects.","start":3350.158,"stop":3361.914,"duration":11.76},{"text":"It could be supervision of --","start":3361.914,"stop":3364.196,"duration":2.28}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I think that the problem that Justice Black is referring to is the unlawful delegation of authority, in other words, if you don't have a State agency, if you -- I don't believe you can delegate governmental authorities to a completely private agency.","start":3364.196,"stop":3376.003,"duration":11.81}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":3376.003,"stop":3376.435,"duration":0.43}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"And just -- and say that all the men, all doctors have to run the associate -- medical association without any control by the State itself.","start":3376.435,"stop":3385.351,"duration":8.92}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I understood your associate to say that within the limits of this charter so-called that the -- that the Supreme Court gave to the legal profession that they had autonomy and that they have absolute independence to act as they see fit and that is to those manners the Court -- the Court did not supervise that.","start":3385.351,"stop":3412.795,"duration":27.44}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"That's a -- that's substantially --","start":3412.795,"stop":3414.403,"duration":1.61}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"And that those are the things that are complained of.","start":3414.403,"stop":3416.939,"duration":2.54},{"text":"Those -- those so-called political activities are the things that are being complained of.","start":3416.939,"stop":3422.911,"duration":5.97},{"text":"Now, my question is, could they do the same thing with every other profession that the State regulates them and I think most States do regulate or --","start":3422.911,"stop":3433.53,"duration":10.62}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think it presents a constitutional problem.","start":3433.53,"stop":3435.764,"duration":2.23},{"text":"The question is wise policy but I think their association is different that you're dealing with officers of the Court to start out with.","start":3435.764,"stop":3443.313,"duration":7.55}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"They're not officers of the -- they're officers of the Court when it comes to employing a -- a lobbyist that the legislature to -- to represent views of the majority against the minority?","start":3443.313,"stop":3455.578,"duration":12.26},{"text":"That that isn't practiced at all, is it for regulating their activities?","start":3455.578,"stop":3461.051,"duration":5.47}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I think it's a -- it's done for the purpose of improving the administration of justice.","start":3461.051,"stop":3464.698,"duration":3.65}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, yes.","start":3464.698,"stop":3465.908,"duration":1.21},{"text":"I don't doubt that at all.","start":3465.908,"stop":3468.38,"duration":2.47},{"text":"But what I'm trying to find out General, is it -- if there's any distinction, legal -- constitutional distinction between such activities of the State Bar and such activities of any other profession or business or employment?","start":3468.38,"stop":3486.618,"duration":18.24}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"I would -- I don't think so.","start":3486.618,"stop":3488.269,"duration":1.65},{"text":"In other words, I think if you took the medical society and have an interfering medical society and they want to express their views on health problem, there's no reason why they couldn't express their views.","start":3488.269,"stop":3497.297,"duration":9.03},{"text":"At the same time, we're going to keep in mind they were not the same as the minority in that association could not express its views too.","start":3497.297,"stop":3505.547,"duration":8.25}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":3505.547,"stop":3505.927,"duration":0.38}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"There was no one that was being silenced by the integrated bar or by this method of regulation.","start":3505.927,"stop":3511.26,"duration":5.33}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":3511.26,"stop":3511.896,"duration":0.64}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"They're not being silenced.","start":3511.896,"stop":3512.945,"duration":1.05},{"text":"That complaint is at least in one respect that a part of their money taken out of their pocket against their will and put in to a collective fund, part of which is used for the propagation of political ideas that they are against.","start":3512.945,"stop":3530.553,"duration":17.61}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that's a hypothetical question.","start":3530.553,"stop":3533.268,"duration":2.72},{"text":"It is in this case --","start":3533.268,"stop":3534.17,"duration":0.9}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that's not a hypothetical question.","start":3534.17,"stop":3535.725,"duration":1.55},{"text":"That's what I understand to be done.","start":3535.725,"stop":3537.436,"duration":1.71}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"He hasn't named what he is against though on the record.","start":3537.436,"stop":3539.908,"duration":2.47}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What is that?","start":3539.908,"stop":3540.713,"duration":0.81}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"On the record of this case, he hasn't complained of any -- of any -- he hasn't named any Act that he's against.","start":3540.713,"stop":3545.645,"duration":4.93}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it -- it wasn't that agreed to between you that there were?","start":3545.645,"stop":3550.896,"duration":5.25}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"No, no.","start":3550.896,"stop":3551.806,"duration":0.91},{"text":"There has been a great -- on the record in this case --","start":3551.806,"stop":3553.691,"duration":1.88}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Are you -- are you then depending on the basis of the -- not that you could do that but does the record doesn't show that you --","start":3553.691,"stop":3562.474,"duration":8.78}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I want to point that out but I want to answer your question.","start":3562.474,"stop":3565.14,"duration":2.67}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well is that what you're depending on that if this record doesn't show that you have done that?","start":3565.14,"stop":3570.706,"duration":5.57}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I want to point it out.","start":3570.706,"stop":3571.919,"duration":1.21},{"text":"But I also wish to answer the question.","start":3571.919,"stop":3574.779,"duration":2.86}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, but --","start":3574.779,"stop":3575.663,"duration":0.88}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"In the sense --","start":3575.663,"stop":3575.99,"duration":0.33}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- would you raise that question because that raises a different question to what I thought you would raise?","start":3575.99,"stop":3580.665,"duration":4.68}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, in the record of this case, the complainant, the petitioner has never complained of a single Act.","start":3580.665,"stop":3588.515,"duration":7.85},{"text":"He's never named the Act of the State Bar.","start":3588.515,"stop":3588.704,"duration":0.19},{"text":"He has never availed himself of his remedies, Your Honor, to go to the Supreme Court of Wisconsin and say, Your Honors, the Bar is violating the law of the State by its activities.","start":3588.704,"stop":3600.108,"duration":11.4}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, has he claimed that it's violating the law of the State?","start":3600.108,"stop":3604.509,"duration":4.4}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":3604.509,"stop":3605.153,"duration":0.64},{"text":"Or that is the --","start":3605.153,"stop":3606.522,"duration":1.37}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I understood him to say that it was violating the law of the Constitution.","start":3606.522,"stop":3610.272,"duration":3.75}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the -- the Constitution in Wisconsin is substantially the same as the Constitution of United States.","start":3610.272,"stop":3614.731,"duration":4.46}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":3614.731,"stop":3615.033,"duration":0.3}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"But as to the question of using the fees which are licensed fees in the same category, this I believe goes on everyday.","start":3615.033,"stop":3622.799,"duration":7.77},{"text":"We have a judicial counsel in Madison, Wisconsin and they make recommendations to legislature.","start":3622.799,"stop":3628.301,"duration":5.5},{"text":"Our conservation department -- we -- we collect money from every -- fees from every county in Wisconsin, there were 500,000 of them and we take those fees the conservation department does --","start":3628.301,"stop":3638.34,"duration":10.04}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"That's the Government, isn't it?","start":3638.34,"stop":3639.886,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"That's the Government.","start":3639.886,"stop":3640.798,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":3640.798,"stop":3641.341,"duration":0.54},{"text":"Well, it --","start":3641.341,"stop":3641.995,"duration":0.65}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"But this Your Honor is the Government too.","start":3641.995,"stop":3644.088,"duration":2.09},{"text":"The State Bar is a State agency.","start":3644.088,"stop":3646.106,"duration":2.02},{"text":"That's why I'm here as their -- as the Attorney General defending them.","start":3646.106,"stop":3649.685,"duration":3.58}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"This is the Government which as through your judges has set up a system under which a man to get the right to practice law has to belong to the Bar association.","start":3649.685,"stop":3659.175,"duration":9.49},{"text":"And he's complaining not that he has to be a lawyer, it maybe that they are raising here the question they can't do that at all, but they're certainly raising the distinct question that you cannot require them to belong to association and pay their dues and then use them to propagate ideas that they're against.","start":3659.175,"stop":3676.664,"duration":17.49}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, if he belongs to the association before it's integrated.","start":3676.664,"stop":3680.384,"duration":3.72}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that's quite a different thing.","start":3680.384,"stop":3683.249,"duration":2.86},{"text":"I -- I presume that nobody has ever raised any question, whether the associate people who belong to a voluntary association somehow I think we have a case on that several years ago.","start":3683.249,"stop":3696.268,"duration":13.02},{"text":"Some others (Inaudible) and some are not, that a voluntary association could spend its own money is it saw fit and they couldn't bar that -- that's a different thing.","start":3696.268,"stop":3707.877,"duration":11.61}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"But this here is --","start":3707.877,"stop":3708.505,"duration":0.63}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"But when you force any one man to -- to contribute money for something he is against is where -- what I understand is one of the questions they raise here.","start":3708.505,"stop":3719.509,"duration":11}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"But Your Honor, to be in the real estate business in Wisconsin, you have to license for the real estate board.","start":3719.509,"stop":3724.727,"duration":5.22},{"text":"The Board itself uses those fees to present its points of view to the legislature before --","start":3724.727,"stop":3729.301,"duration":4.57}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well maybe -- maybe the Board if you have this same setup where you compel the people to pay dues and pay something into it in order to spend it for propaganda purposes might have the same question they have here.","start":3729.301,"stop":3740.744,"duration":11.44},{"text":"I don't know.","start":3740.744,"stop":3741.303,"duration":0.56}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"But I think it's the -- it's the normal way of operating or regulating trades in our society.","start":3741.303,"stop":3747.228,"duration":5.93}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it --","start":3747.228,"stop":3747.297,"duration":0.07}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"But how was the Board created, your real estate board?","start":3747.297,"stop":3750.718,"duration":3.42}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"By act of the legislature.","start":3750.718,"stop":3752.095,"duration":1.38}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, and who -- who fills the position?","start":3752.095,"stop":3754.503,"duration":2.41}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"They're appointed by the governor.","start":3754.503,"stop":3755.899,"duration":1.4}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"By the governor.","start":3755.899,"stop":3756.768,"duration":0.87}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"The realtors have the real --","start":3756.768,"stop":3758.568,"duration":1.8}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Strictly -- strictly a real estate --","start":3758.568,"stop":3760.659,"duration":2.09}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"It's a governmental agency but our position is that the State Bar of Wisconsin is just as much a governmental agency.","start":3760.659,"stop":3767.667,"duration":7.01},{"text":"Is that an example --","start":3767.667,"stop":3768.421,"duration":0.75}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Could they get -- do they get a salary these real estate members?","start":3768.421,"stop":3772.804,"duration":4.38},{"text":"Are they officials of the State?","start":3772.804,"stop":3774.286,"duration":1.48}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":3774.286,"stop":3775.363,"duration":1.08}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Is every lawyer an official of the State under your law?","start":3775.363,"stop":3779.462,"duration":4.1}]},{"speakerName":"John W. Reynolds","textObjs":[{"text":"No, the officer of the Court.","start":3779.462,"stop":3783.845,"duration":4.38},{"text":"He has, of course, certain powers that were given by the Court.","start":3783.845,"stop":3794.989,"duration":11.14},{"text":"Thank you very much.","start":3794.989,"stop":3825.777,"duration":30.79}]}]}],"decidedBy":"Warren Court","arguedOn":"Jan 18, 1961","petitioner":"","respondent":"","docket":"200","citation":"367 US 820 (1961)","justiaLink":"https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/367/820","lowerCourt":"","grantedOn":"","decidedOn":"Jun 19, 1961"}